Commentary: Not much shape to start with! A length ball, outside off. Latham leaves it alone for the keeper to collect it.
On a length and outside off. Latham shoulders arms to it.
Good keeping by Foakes! A full ball, down the leg side. Latham misses his flick and Foakes dives to his right to make a solid stop.
A length ball, way outside off. Latham lets it through to the keeper.
On a length and on off. Latham steps across and defends it right under his eyes.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Broad gets the early breakthrough and Tom Latham goes without troubling the scorers! Broad sets the tone as he keeps serving in the outside off channel, this one is on a length and angling just outside off. Latham could have left this one as well but tries to defend it and it takes the outside edge and goes to first slip where Joe Root takes at a good height. He doesn't drop many. England off to a bright start!
Howout: c Joe Root b Stuart Broad

Commentary: Superb delivery from Potts! A full ball, just around the 5th stump channel. Young gets low to defend but the ball nips away and beats the outside edge.
On a length and outside off. Young leaves it alone.
New Zealand and Will Young are underway! On a length and on the pads, it is flicked past square leg for a couple of runs.
Length ball, just outside off. Young prods to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
This one just slightly comes back in, on a length and outside off. Young shoulders arms to it.
Fuller ball, around off. Young keeps it out on the leg side.

FOUR! Williamson almost falls into the trap! Short of a length and slanting on the hips. Williamson flicks it fine and there is a leg slip standing but the ball goes in the gap, past the keeper and into the fine leg fence. Williamson is underway as well.
Bowls it on a length and on middle, Kane Williamson defends it back towards Matthew Potts.
On a length and slanting on top of off. Williamson taps it to point.
Near the off-stump channel. Williamson blocks it to point.
Length ball, way outside off. Williamson makes an easy leave.

Wow! A beauty from Broad to end the over! A length ball, around off, it jags away off the pitch and Williamson is beaten on the outside edge as he looks to defend. Broad was interested for a while but no support for him from the skipper.
Outside off. Left alone.
FOUR! First real shot of the session! A length ball, outside off. Young hangs back and punches it past the diving point fielder and the ball races quickly into the fence.
Length and on middle. Defended out solidly.
Length ball, outside off. Young lets it through.
On a length and outside off, the ball dies and drifts in off the deck. Young looks to pull but misses and the keeper again makes a very good stop, this time to his left.
Length ball, way outside off. Will shoulders arms to it.
Length and on middle, tucked behind square on the leg side for a single.
Fuller ball, outside off. Young leaves it alone to the keeper.
A length ball, angling around middle and leg. Young misses his flick and gets hit high on the pads.
Fuller ball on off. Young looks to drive but the bat turns in his hands and goes through the mid-wicket region for a brace.
Way outside off. Easy leave for WiIl.
Full again on middle, it is flicked to mid-wicket.
A length ball, outside off, a bit of extra bounce as well. Williamson looks to cut but misses.
On a length and on middle, Kane Williamson defends it back towards the bowler.
This is full and on off. Williamson looks to push but inner edges it to deep square leg for a single.
Full and slanting on middle. Young defends it out.
Too full this time on middle. Young on drives it but straight to mid on.
A length ball, outside off at 134 clicks. Young looks to play at it but pulls his bat out in the end.
Three runs! A full ball, straight on the pads. Williamson flicks it past square leg. The fielder gives a chase and does well to keep it away from the fence and save a single.

A direct hit and Young was in serious trouble! Length and on middle. Young nudges it to mid-wicket and calls for a quick single. The fielder there has a shy at the bowler's end but the angle was tight and he misses.
Length and on middle. Kept out.
Outside off, on a length. Kane leaves it alone.
On a length and outside off. Williamson makes another leave.
A length ball from wide of the crease and outside off. Williamson shoulders arms to it.
Just short of the fielder! A full ball, slanting outside off. Young lunges and looks to defend with soft hands but gets a thick outside edge and it lands well in front of Pope at the fourth slip.
Length and outside off. Young leaves it alone.
Outside off. Young is not interested to play at it.
Potts targets the stumps and Young gets a straight bat down to keep it out.
A length ball, around middle and leg. Young turns it to deep square leg and rotates the strike.
This is way outside off, fuller and Williamson lets it through to the keeper.
This one comes back in but from the outside off channel. Young covers his stumps and leaves it alone.
Much better! Angles a full ball, around off, Young stays back and tucks it to square leg for a single.
On a length and outside off. Williamson shuffles across and blocks it. He was ready to show his football skills as the ball bounces just near the off stump.
FOUR! Beautifully timed! Overpitched from Broad, outside off. Williamson drives it crisply through covers for a boundary.
Similar line and length as the previous delivery and Kane leaves it alone.
On a length and around off at 132 kph. Williamson was a bit hurried as he defends this out.
Overton starts with a short ball, outside off. Young lets it through to the keeper.
Hits the hard length at 134 kph. Left alone.
Length and on middle, hint of shape there. Young stays behind the line to block it.
FOUR! Good shot! This is very wide and on the shorter side. Young frees his arms and punches it with full control and through covers for a boundary.
Goes fuller now, on off, pushed to mid off.
This is very full and swinging on middle. Young blocks it out solidly. So, 4 runs from his debut over.
On a good length, outside off, Kane Williamson defends solidly.
Stuart Broad goes slightly back of a length, outside off, Kane Williamson taps it with soft hands towards point for a single.
Stuart Broad goes full, outside off at 130kmph, Will Young leaves it alone.
Persists with the line outside off on a good length, Will Young fends it towards gully.
Stuart Broad goes back of a length outside off. Will Young attempts to pull this but gets an inside edge onto his pads. Could have easily gone onto the stumps!
Back-of-a-length delivery once again, but closer to the body. Will Young connects the pull to deep sqaure leg for a single.
On a good length, outside off, Jamie Overton gets some extra bounce and Will Young defends it well towards gully.
Shorter this time, on middle, Will Young pulls this through mid-wicket and gets three.
Jamie Overton goes outside off on a good length, Kane Williamson defends this well towards gully.
Jamie Overton brings the length back and goes shorter outside off, Kane Williamson ducks and lets this one through to the keeper.
Full swinging delivery on off, Kane Williamson knocks this through backward point for a single.
Yorker length on middle, Will Young brings his bat down on time and works it to mid-wicket for a single.

OUT! LBW! What a start for Jack Leach! Will Young has reviewed it. That is dead in front of the wicket and there is no inside edge. Will Young makes the long walk to the pavilion. This was full on middle, Will Young tries to work it leg side but misses the line of the delivery, perhaps his bat got stuck behind the front pad a bit and came ahead late. It goes and thuds onto the pads. An appeal and the umpire gives it out, Young goes for the review but the Ball Tracking shows three reds and New Zealand lose their review.
Howout: lbw b Jack Leach

Commentary: Flatter on off, defended back to the bowler.
Full and angled into the stumps, Devon Conway knocks it mid on.
FOUR! Good way to get off the mark! Flighted full outside off, hardly any turn for the bowler. Devon Conway steps forward and crunches it through cover for a boundary!
Full delivery outside off, keeps its line and goes straight, Gets a thick outside edge to backward point.
Flighted wide from off stump, Defended back to the bowler.
Short heading down leg side. Kane Williamson leaves this one alone.
Full, outside off, left alone once again.
Full but closer to the stumps. Driven firmly to cover.
Shorter and outside off, Kane Williamson leaves it through and towards the keeper.
Bowls it on a length and on off, Kane Williamson flicks it towards mid-wicket for one.
Back of a length delivery shaping it into the batter, Devon Conway makes a tight leave. This was close.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Kane Williamson blocks it away.
Tossed up on middle again, Kane Williamson defends it back towards Jack Leach.
This was similar to the last delivery, Kane Williamson eases it back towards the bowler again.
On middle again, Kane Williamson guides it towards the mid on fielder.
On off, defended out.
A maiden from Jack Leach. Tossed up on off, Kane Williamson cuts it towards the fielder at point.
Bowls a fuller one outside off, Devon Conway looks to play at it but misses.
On a length with some extra bounce and into the batter, Devon Conway looks to block it but misses. The ball hits his pads and rolls back towards the bowler.
Goes outside off this time, Devon Conway leaves it alone.
Outside off again angling it away, Devon Conway leaves it towards the keeper.
Goes outside leg this time, Devon Conway looks to pull it but misses.
Single to finish the over. This is fuller and down the middle, Devon Conway flicks it towards square leg for one.
FOUR! Takes the charge! Tossed up on off, Devon Conway dances down the track and lofts it over mid on for a one-bounce boundary.
On middle this time, Devon Conway flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Kane Williamson defends it back towards Jack Leach.
Bowls it on off this time, Kane Williamson flicks it but finds the fielder at mid on.
On middle and fuller in length, Kane Williamson eases it back towards Jack Leach.
This was similar to the last delivery, Kane Williamson defends it solidly.
Back of a length and down the middle, Devon Conway pulls it hard but finds the fielder at deep square leg. Single taken.
Shorter one this time, Kane Williamson ducks underneath it.
Slightly shorter and on leg, Kane Williamson defends it towards the vacant silly point region.
FOUR! Fuller one this time, Kane Williamson nudges it towards long on. Stuart Broad gives it a chase but only escorts the ball towards the fence.
Outside off this time, left alone by Kane Williamson.
On a length and on middle, Kane Williamson flicks it to square leg for one.
Fuller and on middle, Kane Williamson blocks it away.

FOUR! Fuller and on middle, Kane Williamson uses his feet and looks to loft it over long on. He gets a leading edge as the ball goes over mid off but clears the fielder there. Kane Williamson gets a lucky escape.
On off, defended out.
Full again on the middle, Kane Williamson plays it to wide mid on area.
FOUR! Second boundary off the over. Quicker on a good length and outside off as well, Kane Williamson guides it towards the third man region for a boundary.
Bowls it on off, Kane Williamson guides it towards gully.
On off, defended out.
On a length and on middle, Devon Conway fumbles a bit but defends it out solidly.
On a length outside off, Devon Conway leaves it alone.
On middle this time, Devon Conway blocks it back towards Matthew Potts.
Bowls it outside off, Devon Conway leaves it through and towards the keeper.
A maiden from Matthew Potts. Outside off again, Devon Conway shoulders arms at it.
Good-length delivery on middle, Kane Williamson blocks it on the front foot.
Full on the pads, worked towards long on for a single.
Over the wicket, flighted full on middle, Devon Conway defends solidly.
Jack Leach flights it once again outside off, driven firmly to covers.
Quicker and on off, Devon Conway defends it away.
Flighted up on middle, Devon Conway plays a reverse sweep but finds the fielder at backward point.
On a good length and outside off, Kane Williamson lets it go to the keeper.
Full and on middle. Defended back to the bowler.
Full swinging delivery outside off stump, Kane Williamson leaves it alone.
Back of a length on off stump. Defended back down the pitch.
Full and angled into the pads, Kane Williamson gets his bat down and gets an inside edge towards backward square leg for a single.
Good-length delivery on off, Devon Conway strides forward and defends it back to Matthew Potts.
Stuart Broad starts off with a good-length delivery outside off stump. Kane Williamson happy to let it go through the keeper.
Stuart Broad goes fuller this time outside off, Kane Williamson leaves it alone again.
Stuart Broad bowls the same delivery, Kane Williamson puts his bat down to this one and fends it towards gully.
Slighly shorter but still outside off, and that allows Kane Williamson to leave it alone.
On a good length, pitching on off stump. Nips back sharply and hits the pads. Going over the stumps.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Kane Williamson edges this one and walks! Stuart Broad has been brought into the attack and the move works! The New Zealand skipper has to depart. The delivery is bowled on a good length, outside off. Kane Williamson is unsure whether to play at it or leave and in the end just hangs his bat undecisively. Gets a slight edge and Ben Foakes takes an easy catch. England players appeal and the umpire is unmoved but Kane Williamson turns around and walks! Three down now for New Zealand!
Howout: c Ben Foakes b Stuart Broad

Commentary: On a length and down the middle, Devon Conway eases it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off shaping it away, Devon Conway leaves it alone.
Much fuller and outside off, Devon Conway looks to defend it but misses.
This is fuller and on leg, Devon Conway looks to flick it but the ball hits his pads and rolls towards square leg fielder. Single taken.
Full and outside off stump. Henry Nicholls puts his bat down to defend and the ball hits the bat hard.
Short and wide delivery outside off, going further away with the swing, Henry Nicholls tries hard to reach for it and slash at it. Misses the delivery and should probably be leaving that one alone.
Broad bowls from around the wicket and angles into Devon Conway. Defended it firmly.

DROPPED! Tough chance for Ben Foakes! Stuart Broad bowls this on a good length, outside off, Swings in considerably and gets an inside edge of Devon Conway's blade. Flies just over the stumps and Ben Foakes dives to his right and gets his gloves to it. Massive let-off for Devon Conway!
Full on off stump, Henry Nicholls gets across the stumps and defends it towards cover.
Full and outside off, Henry Nicholls lets it go to the keeper.
Full delivery outside off. Steered towards backward point for an easy single. Henry Nicholls is off the mark.
Back-of-a-length delivery outside off. Devon Conway gets on top of it and defends it well.
On a length and outside leg, Henry Nicholls looks to flick it but misses.
This one is outside off, Henry Nicholls shoulders arms at it.
Outside off again, Henry Nicholls leaves it alone towards the keeper.
Fuller and down the middle, Henry Nicholls guides it towards the mid on fielder.
On off and fuller in length, Henry Nicholls drives it but finds the fielder at short covers.
A maiden from Matthew Potts. On off again, Henry Nicholls defends it towards short cover.
On a length and outside off, Devon Conway guides it towards the fielder at gully.
On a length and outside off, Devon Conway leaves it alone.
This was similar to the last delivery, Devon Conway shoulders arms at it.
Goes fuller this time, Devon Conway flicks it towards the mid on region.
Bowls it outside off again, Devon Conway leaves it alone.
Another maiden. Fuller and outside off, Devon Conway guides it towards gully. That will be Lunch on Day 1.
Three runs to start the session! A full ball from around the wicket and angling on the pads. Nicholls flicks it past mid-wicket and Overton does well to pull it back near the fence.
On a length and on off. Conway blocks it out.
Fuller and outside off, it is driven through the left of mid off for a single.
Length ball, outside off. Nicholls leans and blocks it out solidly.
Slightly short and around off. Nicholls hops and taps it to covers.
Short of a length and around off, it nips back in. Nicholls looks to block but gets beaten there. 4 runs to start this session.
A full ball, outside off, swings away. Conway drives it straight to covers.
Angles it onto the pads, it is flicked to mid-wicket.
Leg bye! Slants a full ball on the pads. Conway tries to clip it but fails and it goes off the pads to fine leg. A leg bye.
Fuller and outside off. Left alone.
Outside off, fuller and it moves away off the deck. Nicholls leaves it alone.
Way outside off. Nicholls shoulders arms to it.
A length ball, outside off, it slightly nips in. Conway has his stumps covered as he lets it go.
Full and outside off. Devon works it to short covers.
Touch fuller and outside off. Conway steps down and across to defend but gets an inside edge to fine leg for a single. A bit of ball movement again there.
Fuller ball, outside off. Nicholls shoulders arms.

NOT OUT! A big inswinger, fuller and slanting around middle and off. Nicholls prods and looks to work on the leg side but misses and gets hit on the pads. A huge, huge appeal for LBW but not given. Now then, Stokes, Foakes and Potts get together and eventually take the review. UltraEdge shows there is a spike, but the bat is close to the pads and the third umpire thinks it is off the bat. Ball Tracking though shows three reds but Nicholls is saved by an inside edge.
Length and on off, pushed to covers.
A length ball, outside off, swing again. Conway leaves it alone.
FOUR! Well played! Straight on the pads. Conway flicks it past mid-wicket and it races away into the fence.
On middle, blocked out.
On a length and outside off. Conway drops it to point. Nicholls is thinking for a single but is sent back.
FOUR! Second one of the over! Pitched up, outside off. Conway drives it late past point for a boundary.
Length and outside off. Left alone.
On a length and on off. Nicholls punches it to mid off.
This is full and around off, nipping in. Nicholls prods and defends it out.
Fuller ball, outside off. Nicholls lets it through this time.
Length ball, outside off. Nicholls punches off the back foot to backward point.
On middle, on a length, tucked to square leg.
Touch fuller and around off. Nicholls drives it off the inside half of the bat and back to the bowler.

Superb delivery! On a length and drifting around off. Conway looks to defend but steep bounce hits him on the gloves. The pitch is certainly assisting more to the bowlers as compared to the first session.
On middle, kept out.
FOUR! Really good shot! This is full and just outside off. Conway drives it straight past Broad for a boundary.
Tries to shape back in but bowls it down the leg side. Conway looks to flick but misses and it brushes the thigh pads on its way to the keeper.
Short in length and on off. Conway dead bats it.
Fuller ball, outside off. Conway shoulders arms to it.
On a length and near to the off stump line but wide enough for Nicholls to shoulders arms.
Length ball, outside off. Nicholls gets low and cuts it hard but straight to point.
Very full and on off. Nicholls is a bit hurried as he looks to work on the leg side but miscues his shot on the off side.
A length ball, outside off. Left alone.
This is very good bowling from Potts! Consistency! Again angles a full ball, around off. Nicholls is finding it hard to play this one as he is rushed again to defend it.
Full and on off. Henry blocks it out solidly.
A full ball, slanting across, outside off. Conway opens the face of the bat and plays it down but the backward point fielder dives to his right and makes a solid stop.
On a length and on the hips. Conway pulls it straight to square leg.

OUT! TIMBER! Maiden Test wicket for Jamie Overton! He is pumped up! His twin brother, Craig Overton watches it from the pavilion and celebrates! What a moment for the Englishman! Overton serves a full ball, angling away from Conway and there is a late in-swing as well. Devon Conway is a bit early as he leans and looks to drive but gets a thick inside edge and the ball ricochets onto the stumps. Jamie Overton is delighted as he celebrates his first wicket.
Howout: b Jamie Overton

Commentary: This is way down the leg side. Easy leave.
Bangs a bouncer, around off. Mitchell ducks under it.
Fuller and on off. Mitchell comes forward and blocks it out.
Jack Leach starts over the wicket with a flighted delivery outside off. Henry Nicholls leaves it alone.
Quicker delivery on a good length, angled into the pads. Henry Nicholls works it to square leg for a single.
Full and on middle. Defended back to the bowler.
Full once again outside off, Daryl Mitchell gets across and knocks it to long on for a single.
On a good length outside off, Henry Nicholls uses footwork and defends it on the full.
Slightly short outside off, Fended towards point off the backfoot.
Slightly short and outside off, Daryl Mitchell gets on his toes and defends it back to the bowler.
Jamie Overton bangs it in short. Daryl Mitchell uses his wrists and pulls it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Goes short once again on middle. Henry Nicholls rises high and defends it back to the bowler.
Good-length delivery on the pads. Henry Nicholls works it to square leg for a single.
Back-of-a-length delivery of off stump, Daryl Mitchell defends it well to cover.
Much fuller and on middle, Daryl Mitchell blocks it solidly.
Full and outside off, Knocked towards mid on.
Flighted full around off, Defended firmly.
Tossed up on middle, Henry Nicholls guides it to the mid on fielder.
Back-of-a-length on off, Thumped off the back foot straight to the cover fielder.
Short delivery on middle. Spinning down leg side and left alone by Henry Nicholls
Flights it once again outside off, Henry Nicholls stays back in the crease and defends.
On a length and on middle, Daryl Mitchell defends it out.
On a good length, Daryl Mitchell eases it towards the leg side for a quick single.
Outside off this time, Henry Nicholls guides it to gully.
Bowls it shorter and down the leg side, Henry Nicholls ducks underneath it.
On a length and on middle, Henry Nicholls flicks it towards the fielder at square leg.
Outside off this time, Henry Nicholls eases it to the gully fielder.
Flighted delivery full and on leg stump, defended towards short leg.
Full and on middle, Defended back to the bowler.
On a good length outside off, Played towards cover.
Straight and full, Defended back to Jack Leach.
Full and straight once again. There is a little bit of flight and Daryl Mitchell defends it back in the air. Falls just short of Jack Leach.
Full and on middle. Daryl Mitchell keeps his bat straight and defends solidly.
On a length and outside off, Henry Nicholls drives it but finds the fielder at short cover.
Outside off again, this is guided towards the mid off fielder who dives to his left to stop it.
Shorter and outside off, Henry Nicholls looks to play at it but misses.
On a length and on middle, Henry Nicholls defends it towards the leg side.
Touch fuller and down the middle, Henry Nicholls guides it to short cover and straight to the fielder.
On middle this time, Henry Nicholls flicks it towards square leg for one.
Tossed up delivery on middle, this is defended back towards Jack Leach.
Fuller and on off, Henry Nicholls looks to sweep it but misses as the ball hits his pads. An appeal but nothing given.
Action replay of the last delivery, this again hits his pads as he looks to sweep it.
Outside off, left alone.
Bowls it on middle and fuller, Henry Nicholls blocks it away.
Fuller nd outside off, Henry Nicholls defends it towards the off side.
Goes fuller on middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell flicks it towards short mid-wicket.
Bowls it outside leg this time, Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone.
FOUR! Slightly shorter and on middle, Daryl Mitchell pulls it hard and through the deep square leg fence for a boundary.
On a good length and on middle, Daryl Mitchell defends it back towards Jamie Overton.
This one is fuller and outside off, Daryl Mitchell looks to drive at it but misses.
Touch fuller and outside off, Daryl Mitchell shoulders arms at it.
Fuller and on off, Henry Nicholls flicks it towards the leg side.
Tossed up delivery on off, Henry Nicholls flicks it to mid on and gets a single.
Outside off, Daryl Mitchell guides it towards the fielder at short cover.
On middle this time, Daryl Mitchell eases it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Daryl Mitchell looks to defend it but gets a thick outside edge as the ball rolls towards gully.
Fuller and on middle, this is nudged towards short mid-wicket.
Shorter one on middle, Henry Nicholls ducks under it.
Shorter one again, Henry Nicholls ducks again and lets it go.
Back of a length and on middle, Henry Nicholls flicks it towards the leg side.
Lands it on off and fuller in length, Henry Nicholls guides it towards the mid on region.
Shorter and on middle and leg, Henry Nicholls lets it go.
On a length and on middle, Henry Nicholls pulls it towards backward square leg for one.
Full and outside off, Henry Nicholls tries to sweep and misses, the ball hits the pads.
Good-length delivery on middle. Henry Nicholls goes back on the crease and works it to square leg for a single.
Full delivery just outside off, angling into the stumps. Daryl Mitchell defends and gets an inside edge onto pads.
Daryl Mitchell goes for the reverse sweep. This is full on leg, Daryl Mitchell plays it towards short third man and does not time it well. Stuart Broad makes a diving stop.
Full and on off, Daryl Mitchell gives it the charge and hits in the air towards mid off. A misfield allows them to take a single.
Good-length delivery on middle. Henry Nicholls goes back and knocks it to mid-wicket.
On a length and on middle, Daryl Mitchell defends it solidly.
Good-length delivery on off, Daryl Mitchell defends it back to the bowler.
Full and on off stump. Defended towards the offside.

Massive appeal! Why have they not reviewed this! The ball pitches full and angling into the pads. Hits Daryl Mitchell low on his pads and he plays all over the delivery. Matthew Potts and the rest of the English players are convinced that this is shattering the stumps but the umpire remains unmoved. Ben Stokes decides against taking the review and what a poor decision that is. Ball Tracking shows three reds and the man in form, Daryl Mitchell was out of here!
Fuller and on middle, Daryl Mitchell flicks it towards square leg for one.
On off this time, Henry Nicholls guides it straight towards the fielder at short cover.
Fuller and on middle, this is defended back towards Jack Leach.
FOUR! Tossed up delivery on middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell sweeps it through square leg for a boundary. This was well-timed by Daryl Mitchell.
Full on off stump. Defended towards covers.
Full once again on the pads. Daryl Mitchell fends it towards short mid on.

FOUR! Second boundary of the over! Daryl Mitchell goes for the reverse sweep once again and beats Stuart Broad at short third man this time. Jack Leach bowls this full outside off. and Daryl Mitchell connects this well to get a boundary!
Good-length delivery on the pads. Worked towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Henry Nicholls connects this one well! Full and on middle asking to be hit. Henry Nicholls gets this straight past mid on for a boundary!
Length ball angling into the batter. Tucked away to square leg.
Goes good length once again outside off, Henry Nicholls leaves it alone.
Same length outside off. Henry Nicholls shoulders arms once again.
On a length and outside off, Henry Nicholls lets it through and towards the keeper.
Pulls a length ball towards square leg for a brace.

SIX! That is the first six of the game! Jack Leach flights this one full on middle. Daryl Mitchell gives it the charge and thumps it handsomely over long off for a biggie! Mitchell has been great against spin this series and his form continues.
Full outside off, defended back to the bowler.
Full again on middle. Played towards short mid on.
Jack Leach bowls full once again on middle. Daryl Mitchell defends it back towards him.
Pulls his length back slightly on middle, Daryl Mitchell works it towards short mid on.
Full, angling into the pads. Daryl Mitchell rolls his wrists and fends towards mid-wicket.
On a length and down the middle, Henry Nicholls defends it back towards the bowler.
Goes outside off this time, Henry Nicholls drives it but finds the fielder at short cover.
Bowls it outside off shaping it away, Henry Nicholls shoulders arms at it.
Outside leg and fuller in length, Henry Nicholls looks to flick it but misses. Good stop by Ben Foakes who stops it diving to his right.
On middle and fuller, Henry Nicholls flicks it towards the leg side. A misfield by the fielder costs them one run.
Bowls it outside off this time, Daryl Mitchell lets it through and towards the keeper.
Fuller and quicker on middle, Henry Nicholls defends it solidly.
Outside off, Henry Nicholls looks to cut it but miscues it towards short third man.
Bowls it outside off again, Henry Nicholls looks to defend it but misses.
Goes fuller and on middle, Henry Nicholls eases it back towards Jack Leach.
On a length and outside off, this is guided towards the fielder at point.
Flatter and on middle, Henry Nicholls defends it solidly. A maiden by Jack Leach.
Fuller and outside off, Daryl Mitchell drives it towards the fielder at short cover.
This was similar to the last delivery, Daryl Mitchell again drives it to the short cover fielder.
On a length and outside off, Daryl Mitchell guides it towards mid off this time.
Lands it on a length and outside off, Daryl Mitchell shoulders arms at it.
Outside off again by Matthew Potts, left alone by Daryl Mitchell.
A maiden from Matthew Potts. Lands it on a length and outside off, Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone.
Tossed up outside off, Henry Nicholls uses his feet and defends it towards mid on.
On middle this time, Henry Nicholls defends it solidly.
Slightly shorter and outside off with a hint of turn, Henry Nicholls looks to cut it but misses.
Bowls it on middle and on a good length, this is flicked towards long on for one.
On middle and fuller, Daryl Mitchell defends it away.
Fuller again, this is blocked out solidly.
Fuller and on leg, Henry Nicholls looks to defend it but the ball hits his pads.
Goes outside leg, Henry Nicholls looks to flick it but misses.
Bowls it on middle, Henry Nicholls flicks it towards the leg side and rotates the strike.
Fuller and outside off, Daryl Mitchell sweeps it early towards fine leg for a brace.
Bowls it outside off with a hint of turn, Daryl Mitchell blocks it solidly.
On off, defended out.
Full delivery, bowled quicker and angled into the pads. Worked towards mid-wicket.

OUT! CAUGHT! That is one of the most unbelievable wickets to fall in a Test match! Henry Nicholls will consider himself extremely unlucky because a well-played shot has resulted in a wicket! Jack Leach bowls this full on off, and Henry Nicholls gives it the charge and middles the ball straight back. He, unfortunately, plays it in the direction of Daryl Mitchell who tries to get out of the way but leaves his bat hanging! The ball hits the middle of Daryl Mitchell's bat, who was looking to get away from it and lobs towards mid off where Alex Lees takes an easy catch! England rejoice and Henry Nicholls hangs his head down and takes the long walk off the field! The rest of the players follow as it shall be Tea on DAY 1!
Howout: c Alex Lees b Jack Leach

Commentary: Tossed up on middle. Blocked out.
Tossed up again, around off. Blundell prods and defends it out.
Flatter and outside off. Blundell punches off the back foot through point for a single.
Tossed up angling around middle and leg. Mitchell tucks it to square leg.
FOUR! Freebie! A low full toss, around off. Blundell whips it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Tossed up, fuller and outside off. Blundell stays back and keeps it out.
Fuller ball, around off. Tom defends on the front foot.
Fuller, wide of off. Blundell drives it through covers for a single.
Too full and outside off. Mitchell steps across and sweeps it behind square on the leg side for a brace.
Similar to the previous delivery! Full and outside off, swept to fine leg for a couple of runs.
Tossed up on middle. Blundell gets on the back foot to block it out.
Slightly short and on middle. Blundell rocks back and flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Fuller ball, around off. Blundell blocks it back to the bowler. Consistency here from Leach.
Angling on middle, nudged to square leg.
Tossed up on off. Blundell strides forward and defends it out.
Full ball, angling on middle. Blundell tickles it straight to short fine leg. Tight from Leach.
Tossed up, outside off, it spins away. Mitchell prods to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Fuller and outside off. Mitchell looks to reverse sweep it but misses.
This time he connects the reverse sweep but hits it straight to point.
Full and on off, pushed to covers.
On middle, fuller, Mitchell eases it to long on for a single.
Too full and outside off. Blundell steps across and keeps it out. Tidy from Joe Root.
Tossed up, full and on off. Mitchell knocks it to covers.
Fuller and on middle, spinning in. Blocked out.
Almost a yorker from Leach on middle. Mitchell does well to block it out. An appeal but it came off the bat.
Around off, stroked to covers.
Quicker, fuller and on leg. Mitchell reverse-hits it to deep point for a couple.
On middle, fuller, defended out.
Fullish delivery, outside off. Blundell squeezes it out on the off side.
Sharp single! Fuller and outside off. Blundell skips down and wrists it to mid on and scampers across for a quick single. Comfortably home.
Too full and outside off. Mitchell sweeps it but straight to the fielder at short fine leg.
Flatter and outside off. Mitchell waits and plays it very fine to third man for a brace.
Full and on off. Mitchell taps it in front of covers and takes a quick single. Good running there. New Zealand are scoring runs at quick rate in this session.
Fuller and outside off. Blundell comes down the track and whips it straight to mid on. No run this time.
Shorter and way outside off. Mitchell punches it straight to the cover fielder.
Touch short and outside off. Mitchell punches it through covers and sweeper cover comes across to cut it down. Two more.
Too full and on middle. Mitchell dances down the track and drives it to long on for one more.
Tossed up, on middle, slower in the air. Blundell gets on the front foot to block it.
Sees Blundell coming down the track and bowls it quicker and down the leg side. He flicks it through square leg for a single.
On middle, blocked out.
A length ball, outside off, stays low. Blundell leaves it alone.
On a length and slanting around off. Blundell stays behind the line of the ball to block it.
Full ball on the pads. Tom bunts it to mid-wicket.
Fuller ball on middle. Blundell is solid in his defense.
Length ball, angling on top of off. Another solid block from Blundell.
A length ball from wide of the crease and outside off. Blundell shoulders arms to it.
Tossed up on off. Blocked out.
Keeps bowling around off. Mitchell is happy to keep it out.
Tossed up on middle. Mitchell reverse sweeps and the man at first slip is quick to anticipate as he walks across and cuts it out.
On off, kept out.
FOUR! Runs after quite a while! Touch fuller and slightly slower on middle. Mitchell sweeps it to square leg for a boundary.
Fuller and on middle. Mitchell prods and defends it. 150 up for the Kiwis.
Fuller and outside off. Blundell pushes it to mid off.
Full ball, around off and it nips back in. Blundell leans and looks to work on the leg side but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! This is full and on off. Blundell lunges and shows the full face of the bat as he drives it through mid off for a boundary.
Full again, outside off, it is pushed to mid off this time.
Fuller ball on off. Blundell watchfully blocks it.
Fuller ball, outside off. Blundell guides it to point this time.
Good-length delivery angling into the pads, Daryl Mitchell works it to backward square leg and rushes for a single. The fielder collects and takes an aim at the non-striker's end but misses.
Short and wide. Tom Blundell rocks back and slashes it to deep point for a single.
Daryl Mitchell tries reverse sweep and misses. Full and outside off, hits the batter on the body.
Full on middle, defended back to the bowler.
Full and angling towards the leg side, Daryl Mitchell gets on his knees and tries to sweep. Does not connect and there is an appeal from Jack Leach.
Straight and full, defended to short mid on.
Full on the stumps. Tom Blundell gives the charge and hits it back to the bowler. Joe Root throws it back towards the batter and the keeper collects.
Full outside off, defended solidly.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Tom Blundell cuts it towards backward point and takes a couple of runs.
Tom Blundell charges to a full ball outside off. Knocked towards mid off.
Good-length delivery, spinning in from off stump. Tom Blundell goes on the back foot and gets a single towards cover.
Full delivery on off stump. Defended towards point.
Flighted on off stump. Steps back and punches towards covers.
Similar delivery outside off, Tom Blundell works it wide of covers for a single.
Another reverse sweep from Daryl Mitchell. Full delivery outside off played towards backward point.
Full and on middle. Daryl Mitchell charges at it and flicks it towards mid on.
Slightly short and outside off, Daryl Mitchell gets on his backfoot and plays towards point.
Straight on middle, played back down the pitch for a single.
Tossed-up delivery on middle, Tom Blundell defends it solidly.
Fuller and outside off this time, Tom Blundell cuts it towards backward point. The fielder chases the ball from cover. Three runs taken.
Tossed up outside off, this is eased towards cover for one.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Tom Blundell guides it towards the on side.
Bowls it outside off this time, Tom Blundell punches it to cover for one.
Fuller and outside off, Daryl Mitchell guides it towards covers and takes a single.
Quicker through the air, outside off stump, Daryl Mitchell cuts it towards the sweeper covers for a single.

Huge appeal but nothing comes of it! Tom Blundell comes forward to a full delivery angling down leg stump. Hits him on his pads and there are loud enquiries. The umpire says not out and England do not wish to review.
Full and straying dow leg. Tom Blundell works it fine towards fine leg for three runs.
Straight and on middle. Defended towards short mid on.

SIX! That is another half-century for Daryl Mitchell! He has been in sublime touch! Jack Leach bowls this full on the stumps. Daryl Mitchell shows good footwork to get to the pitch of the delivery and heaves it over long off for the maximum! New Zealand have had a tough time on this tour but Daryl Mitchell has stood out for them!
Good-length delivery on middle. Stands tall and fends towards short mid on.
Bowls it fuller and down the middle, Tom Blundell defends it back towards Joe Root.
On middle again, Tom Blundell guides it to the vacant silly point region.
FOUR! This is perfectly timed by Tom Blundell. On a length and outside off, Tom Blundell makes room for himself and smashes it through point for a boundary.
On off, kept out.

A huge appeal for caught behind and up goes the finger but Blundell was quick to review it and he survives! Bowls it outside off with a hin of turn, Tom Blundell looks to cut it but misses. A loud appeal and the finger goes up. Tom Blundell reviewed it immediately. UltraEdge shows a flat line and the decision is reversed.
Back of a length and on off, Tom Blundell blocks it away.
Tossed up on middle, this is defended towards the vacant short leg region.
Bowls it fuller and on middle, Daryl Mitchell defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off this time, Daryl Mitchell looks to play at it but misses.
Goes fuller and on middle, Daryl Mitchell eases it towards the off side.
On middle and fuller in length, Daryl Mitchell works it towards mid-wicket for one.
Tossed-up delivery on middle, Tom Blundell blocks it away.
Slightly shorter on off, Daryl Mitchell pulls it but finds the fielder at short mid-wicket.
Bowls it on a good length this time, Daryl Mitchell eases it back towards the bowler.
Goes outside leg and away from the batter, Daryl Mitchell looks to flick it but misses.
Slightly shorter and on off, Daryl Mitchell pulls it again but straight to the fielder at short mid-wicket
FOUR! On a length and on leg, Daryl Mitchell uses the pace of the ball and gives it a fine tickle. The ball races towards the fine leg and past the fence.
On a good length and on middle, Daryl Mitchell looks to defend it but the ball hits his thigh and rolls towards the bowler.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Tom Blundell defends it back towards the bowler.
On middle, this is guided towards the leg side.
On a length and outside off, Tom Blundell punches it towards cover.
Bowls it on middle this time, Tom Blundell defends it towards the mid on region.
On off, kept out.
Tossed up on middle, Tom Blundell defends it solidly.
On a length and on stumps, Daryl Mitchell defends it solidly.
On a length and on leg, Daryl Mitchell flicks it towards fine leg for one.
Bowls it on a length and on off, Tom Blundell guides it to backward point for one.
Shorter and on middle, Daryl Mitchell ducks under it.
Touch fuller down the middle, Daryl Mitchell hits it straight towards the bowler who blocks it.
Bowls it outside off, Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone.
Tossed up delivery outside off, this is defended towards gully.
Bowls it on middle and fuller, Tom Blundell eases it back towards the bowler.
FOUR! On a length and outside off, Tom Blundell smashes it through extra cover for a boundary.
Bowls it on a length and on leg, Tom Blundell flicks it towards the leg side.
Touch fuller in length, Tom Blundell punches it towards point and straight towards the fielder.
On a length and down the leg side, Tom Blundell looks to play at it but misses and it goes towards the keeper. A loud appeal but DRS is unavaliabe. Ben Foakes thinks there was bat involved.
Jamie Overton bowls this full on the pads, Daryl Mitchell flicks it towards deep square leg for a single.
Short delivery angling into Tom Blundell. He pulls this to backward sqaure leg.
Connects his pull this time. Jamie Overton bowls this one short as well on middle. Tom Blundell gets a single to deep square leg.
Banged in short again outside off. Daryl Mitchell ducks under this one.

Not out! Jamie Overton bowls this down the leg side on a good length. Daryl Mitchell tries to work this fine but does not connect. Gets a bit of thigh pad on its way and the England players are convinced by the sound. The umpire disagrees and the review has been taken. UltraEdge shows it went off the pads.
Full and angling into the pads. Worked to deep square leg for an easy single.
Lands it fuller and outside off with a hint of turn, Daryl Mitchell guides it to point and takes one.
Goes outside off again, Tom Blundell plays it towards mid off.
Fuller again and down the middle, Tom Blundell blocks it back towards Jack Leach.
On leg this time, Tom Blundell eases it towards the vacant short leg region.
On middle, defended out.
On a length and outside off, Tom Blundell punches it towards the fielder at point.
Banged in short on middle. Daryl Mitchell ducks and leaves it alone.
On a good length, outside off. Daryl Mitchell fends at it and gets a thick outside edge towards backward point for a brace.
Good-length delivery once again, outside off. Daryl Mitchell knocks it back to the bowler.
Short and angled into Daryl Mitchell. He ducks under this easily.
Jamie Overton continues bowling short but gets the line wrong as the ball is angled down leg. Daryl Mitchell is not close but ducks nonetheless.
FOUR! Plays this one fine! Jamie Overton has tried short deliveries all over and gets the radar off on this one as well. Daryl Mitchell pulls and helps it down to fine leg for a boundary!
Tossed up delivery outside off, Tom Blundell blocks it towards the vacant silly point region.
On middle and on a good length, Tom Blundell defends it back towards Jack Leach.
Goes outside off this time, Tom Blundell guides it towards the fielder at mid off.
Much fuller and on middle, Tom Blundell defends it back towards the bowler.
On middle again, this is again defended towards Jack Leach.
Sticks to his line and length, Tom Blundell again eases it towards Jack Leach.
Jamie Overton begins with a straight delivery on a good length. Daryl Mitchell fends it towards point.
Bowls this one slightly full and strays down leg side. Ben Foakes collects this behind the stumps.

FOUR BYES! That looked dangerous! Jamie Overton bowls a waist-high full toss down leg side. Daryl Mitchell misses it in the lights and steps away as the ball narrowly misses the leg stump. Ben Foakes also seems to have lost it and lets it through his legs for four byes.
Full delivery on middle. Defended back to the bowler.
Back-of-a-length delivery on off stump, Daryl Mitchell gets on his backfoot and defends it to covers.
Good length on off, Daryl Mitchell blocks this back down the pitch.
Bowls it on a length and outside off, Tom Blundell guides it towards the fielder at gully.
On leg this time, Tom Blundell flicks it towards mid-wicket and towards the fielder who makes a diving stop.
On middle and fuller in length, Tom Blundell defends it back towards the bowler.
Goes outside off this time, Tom Blundell shoulders arms at it.
Bowls it on a length and on middle, Tom Blundell flicks it towards short mid-wicket. Daryl Mitchell wanted a single but Tom Blundell sends him back.
FOUR! Goes outside off and on a good length, Tom Blundell makes room for himself and punches it through backward point for a boundary.

Stuart Broad starts with a good-length delivery outside off. Daryl Mitchell tries to defend but plays the wrong line as the ball hits the pad. There is an appeal but the impact is clearly outside off stump.
Length delivery on the off stump line, Daryl Mitchell defends it towards covers and straight towards the fielder.
Full outside off, Defended towards covers.
Straighter this time from Stuart Broad and slightly full. Daryl Mitchell hits this uppishly past the bowler straight of mid on. Completes a couple of runs as the fielder runs and collects the ball.
Length ball angling down leg. Daryl Mitchell works this fine for a single.
Good-length delivery on middle. Worked towards mid-wicket by Tom Blundell for a single and retains strike.
Bowls it on a length and down the middle and leg, Tom Blundell defends it towards the mid on region.
Goes outside leg this time, Tom Blundell looks to flick it but misses.
On a length and outside off, Tom Blundell punches it towards the fielder at mid off.
Much fuller in length and outside off, Tom Blundell plays it towards id off and towards the fielder.
Bowls it on middle this time, Tom Blundell defends it back towards the bowler.
On a good length and on middle and leg, Tom Blundell looks to flick it but the ball hits his pads and rolls towards leg gully.
Back-of-a-length delivery outside off. Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone with ease.
Full outside off, Daryl Mitchell knocks this wide of mid off and runs across for a single. The mid off fielder picks up and throws at the non-striker's end. It could have been close had it hit.
Pitched full and outside off. Tom Blundell takes a large stride forward and defends it firmly.
Full on off stump, Tom Blundell shows solid defense.
Same delivery and the exact same result. Tom Blundell looks confident while defending.
Good-length delivery this time, outside off, Tom Blundell bottom edges it towards cover.
Bowls it fuller and on the stumps, Daryl Mitchell defends it towards the mid off region.
On a length and on middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell flicks it but finds the fielder at short mid-wicket.
Outside off this time, Daryl Mitchell drives it towards the fielder at short cover who makes a diving stop.
On middle and on a full length, Daryl Mitchell defends it back towards the bowler.
On middle and much fuller, Daryl Mitchell flicks it towards short mid-wicket and scampers for a quick single.
On off and fuller in length, Tom Blundell guides it towards point and shouts no for a run.
Low full toss, on off. Daryl Mitchell knocks it towards mid off.
Short delivery on middle, Daryl Mitchell pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Short once again from Stuart Broad angling down leg, Tom Blundell pulls this wide of fine leg for a single.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Daryl Mitchell fends this towards point.
Fuller delivery outside off stump. Driven with authority by Daryl Mitchell to mid off.
Full once again outside off, Daryl Mitchell opens the face of the bat and works it through cover-point for a brace.
Bowls it on middle and fuller, Tom Blundell eases it back towards the bowler
Fuller and on middle and leg, Tom Blundell flicks it towards the fielder at leg gully.
On middle and fuller in length, Tom Blundell defends it back towards Jack Leach.
On off this time, this is blocked towards the vacant silly point region.
On middle, blocked out.
Touch fuller in length and outside off, Tom Blundell guides it towards the off side. A maiden from Jack Leach.
Matthew Potts gets this on a good length, outside off. Daryl Mitchell defends this solidly.
Good-length delivery outside off. Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone.
Matthew Potts bowls this on a good length once again, angling in. Daryl Mitchell defends it down the pitch.
Straighter line on a good length. Defended straight back down the pitch.
Full and angling into the pad. Daryl Mitchell flicks it towards midwicket and falls just short of the fielder there. England would have loved that wicket just before stumps.
Full and outside off stump. Worked past point for a single.
Tossed up on middle, this is defended back towards Jack Leach.
Much fuller in length and on middle, Daryl Mitchell works it towards mid-wicket for one. This brings up the 100-run partnership between Daryl Mitchell and Tom Blundell.
On middle with a hint of turn, Tom Blundell tries to defend it with soft hands but gets a thick outside edge as it rolls towards gully.
On middle, blocked out.
Bowls it outside off this time, Tom Blundell steers it towards point for a brace.
Goes fuller and on middle, Tom Blundell defends it solidly. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 1.
A loosener to start with! A low full toss way down the leg side. Mitchell misses his flick and Foakes does well to stop it by diving to his left.
On a length and on middle. Mitchell tucks it to square leg for a single.
Effort ball from Overton! Bangs a bouncer, well-directed on middle. Blundell drops his bat and gets hit on the shoulders. It lobs in front of the keeper. A really good delivery.
Length and on off. Blundell drops it in front of covers for a single.
Length ball, sliding on the pads. Mitchell flicks it to square leg for one more.

FOUR! Boundary to end the over and it also brings up Tom Blundell's half-century! He is having an excellent series till now. On a length and outside off. Blundell opens the face of the bat and steers it past short third man for a boundary. 7 runs to start the proceedings on Day 2.
Fuller ball, outside off. Mitchell drives it crisply but Bairstow makes a good stop at point.
Length and on off. Kept out.
This one is angled around off. Mitchell solidly blocks it.
On a length and outside off. Mitchell shoulders arms to it.

PUT DOWN! Ben Foakes should have left it there for first slip! This is on a length and angling just outside off. Mitchell gets on the front foot and looks to drive but gets a thick outside edge and it goes to first slip but instead, Ben Foakes dives to his right and tries to take it one-handedly and makes a blunder. It rolls behind for a couple of runs. It was meant for Root to catch it. So, Daryl Mitchell survives for the second time in his innings.
On middle. Blocked out.
Length ball, around middle and leg. Blundell tucks it on the leg side.
Short in length and on middle. Blundell pulls it straight to square leg.
FOUR! This time he finds the gap! Short again on middle. Blundell plays the pull this time along the ground and through square leg and it races away behind square leg for a boundary.
Short of a length and on off. Blundell pulls it but finds Bairstow at square leg.
Outside off, left alone.
Length ball, tight on middle. Blundell defends it out.
Fuller and outside off, worked to point.
Full and outside off, hint of away shape. Mitchell lets it through.
Another leave from Mitchell as this is outside off.
Touch fuller and outside off, driven straight to mid off.
Length ball, way, way outside off. Mitchell is happy to leave it.
Better from Potts! Making the batter to play it! He angles a full ball on off. Mitchell pushes it back to Potts.
Length ball, outside off at 135 kph. Blundell shoulders arms to it.
TAP AND RUN! Good running! This is on a length and on off. Blundell knocks it to covers and calls for a quick single.
Four leg byes! Slides one on the pads. Mitchell misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. It rolls quickly to the fine leg fence.
Shorter and around middle and leg. Mitchell tries to take it on as he looks to pull but misses.
Short of a length and on off. Mitchell pulls it straight to square leg.
On off, blocked out.
Length and outside off. Left alone.
Length ball on middle. Blundell nudges it to mid-wicket.

OUT! LBW! Tom Blundell has to go and he cannot even review it as DRS is down again! Finally, England break this stubborn stand and Potts is a happy man! A length ball, slanting around middle and leg. Blundell stays back and tries to work on the leg side but misses and gets hit on the pads. A huge appeal and up goes the finger. The 120-run stand is broken! That was sliding down so, could have been a close call.
Howout: lbw b Matthew Potts

Commentary: A length ball, outside off. Bracewell shoulders arms to it.
Full and on middle, eased to mid on.
Leg bye! Darted on the pads, Bracewell misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. It rolls to square leg for a leg bye.
Short one on middle. Bracewell sits under it.
Another short ball and Bracewell evades it well.
Full and on off, Bracewell pushes it to mid off. Mitchell wants a single but is sent back wisely.
No ball! Overton keeps digging the short ball and Bracewell ducks under it. A no ball given for height!
On middle, blocked out.
Short one again,  Bracewell lets it go for the keeper.
Leg bye! Short in length, on the hips. Bracewell misses his tuck and it rolls off the pads to the leg side for a leg bye.
Outside off, on a length. Left alone.
This one just keeps coming with the angle, length ball, just around off. Bracewell covers his stumps and shoulders arms to it. Tight leave there.
On off, it is nudged to mid-wicket.
Length ball, tailing on the pads. Bracewell tries to wrists it away but misses.
This is way outside off, on a length. Bracewell watchfully leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Hits the hard length and bowls it outside off, Bracewell shoulders arms to it.
Length ball, just around off. Mitchell shuffles across and turns it to mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball, outside off, easy leave for Bracewell.
On a length and outside off, it nips back in but again Bracewell has his stumps covered as he lets it go.
FOUR! Michael Bracewell is off the mark now! A full ball, angling around middle. Bracewell drives it with soft hands and straight down the ground for a boundary.
Outside off, length, left alone.

EDGED AND DROPPED! This time it is Jonny Bairstow and Stuart Broad shakes his head as he walks back. A length ball, outside off, it nips away off the deck. Michael Bracewell looks to push away from the body and without any foot movement. He gets an outside edge to the right of third slip where Bairstow stretches his right hand out but fails to hold onto it. Bracewell now gets a life!
On middle. Blocked out.
This is outside off. Bracewell shoulders arms.
A length ball, outside off, jags away. Bracewell tries to slash at it but misses.
On a length and outside off. Bracewell watches it all the way to the keeper.
There is the variation as Potts bowls one sliding down the leg side. Bracewell misses his flick.
Fuller and just outside off. Bracewell drives it straight but Potts gets low and gets a hand to it. Good stop. 11th maiden over for Potts.
Good-length delivery outside off, Daryl Mitchell defends it down and needs to use his legs to stop the ball from rolling towards the stumps.
Slightly fuller outside off, Daryl Mitchell defends firmly back to the bowler.
Good shape for Stuart Broad. Pitches outside off on a good length. Daryl Mitchell leaves this one alone.
Slightly full once again outside off stump, Daryl Mitchell steps across the stumps and shoulders arms.
On-a-good-length delivery and persists with the outside off stump line, Daryl Mitchell defends this back to Stuart Broad.
Full and wide outside off, Daryl Mitchell fends it towards point.
Full and outside off, defended back down the pitch towards the bowler.
Similar delivery, and Michael Bracewell knocks it towards mid off.
FOUR! Gets a hold of this one! Full and angling into the pads. Michael Bracewell gets on his knees and thumps it towards the mid-wicket boundary to collect four runs!
Good-length delivery outside off, spinning into the batter, Beats Michael Bracewell as it hits his body.
Fuller now outside off, Michael Bracewell leaves it alone.
Outside off stump on a good length, Michael Bracewell strides forward and defends.
Good-length delivery on off, Daryl Mitchell works it towards short mid-wicket.
Straight on a good length. Defends it back to the same fielder.
Sticks to his line and length, this is again blocked towards the fielder at mid on.
On a length and outside off shaping it in, Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone.
Fuller this time and bowls this outside off, Daryl Mitchell defends it back to the bowler.
Wide outside off stump on a good length, Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone and it will be DRINKS!
Flighted full on off, angling in. Michael Bracewell plays it down to long on for a single.
Over the wicket to the right-handed batter, Pitches outside leg and Daryl Mitchell puts his pads to the ball that is turning in.
Back of a length and turning after pitching outside leg. Daryl Mitchell gets on his backfoot and defends it.
Flighted full on leg stump. Daryl Mitchell works it towards square leg.
This is outside leg once again and Daryl Mitchell happy to play with his pads.
Slow-flighted delivery on leg stump. Daryl Mitchell moves his leg away and defends solidly.
Bowls it on a length and around off, Michael Bracewell defends it solidly off the front foot.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Michael Bracewell pulls it towards mid-wicket and takes a couple of runs.
Bowls it on middle this time, Michael Bracewell flicks it towards square leg and straight towards the fielder.
Angling towards leg side from around the wicket on a good length. Works it towards leg square using his thigh pads and gets a leg bye.
Full delivery on off, Daryl Mitchell defends this back down the pitch.
Stuart Broad bowls on a good length and attacks the stumps. Daryl Mitchell defends this back to the bowler.
Tossed up delivery spinning it into the batter, Michael Bracewell looks to play at it but decides to leave it in the end. That was a great delivery from Jack Leach.
Goes fuller and on middle, Michael Bracewell defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it on off with a hint of turn, Michael Bracewell blocks it away.
Goes fuller and on middle, Michael Bracewell gets on his knees and hits it hand but finds the fielder at deep mid-wicket. Single taken.
FOUR! Fuller and down the middle, Daryl Mitchell uses his feet and lofts it over mid on and towards long on for a boundary.
Fuller and down the leg side, Daryl Mitchell defends it with his pads.
On a length and outside off, left alone by Michael Bracewell.
Goes outside off again, Michael Bracewell hits it straight towards Stuart Broad who stops it well.
Bowls it on a length angling it into the batter, Michael Bracewell looks to block it but misses as the ball hits his pads.

OUT! CAUGHT! The birthday boy strikes with the ball and England are happy now! Lands it on a length shaping it into the batter, it holds its line as Michael Bracewell looks to defend it but gets a thick outside edge. The ball carries towards second slip and Zak Crawley does the rest as he takes it low. A perfect gift for the birthday boy and New Zealand look in some trouble now.
Howout: c Zak Crawley b Stuart Broad

Commentary: Tim Southee is welcomed with a full delivery on middle. No swing this time and he defends it back to the bowler.
Stuart Broad goes short this time angled into the batter. Tim Southee ducks under this one and lets it through to the keeper.
Tossed up on middle, this is flicked towards square leg for a quick one.
Fuller in length and down the leg side, Tim Southee guides it towards the short leg fielder.
On middle, Tim Southee defends it back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Fuller and on middle, Tim Southee uses his feet and lofts it just over mid on. A great diving effort from the fielder but just couldn't reach it. The ball races behind the fence for a boundary.
Outside off this time, Tim Southee cuts it towards cover-point and straight towards the fielder.
On middle and fuller in length, Tim Southee defends it solidly.
Fuller length outside off, Daryl Mitchell defends firmly back to the bowler.
Full and angling into the pads, Daryl Mitchell works this wide of mid on and gets a single.
SIX! Slightly shorter in length, Tim Southee uses the pace of the ball and pulls it over the fine leg fence for a maximum.
Shorter one again, Tim Southee guides it towards backward point this time. The fielder does well to stop it at the boundary line. A couple of runs taken.
Shorter one on middle, Tim Southee looks to play at it but misses.
Back of a length and down the middle, Tim Southee defends it back towards Stuart Broad.

On a length and outside leg, Daryl Mitchell looks to give it a fine tickle but the ball brushes his pads and races towards fine leg. Stuart Broad does well and chases it just before the fence. Couple taken.
On off, blocked away.
Slightly shorter and on middle, Daryl Mitchell hops a bit and defends it well.
Bowls it outside leg, Daryl Mitchell looks to flick it but the ball hits his pads.
Tossed up delivery on middle, this is flicked towards the leg side for one. Daryl Mitchell has now scored most runs in a series by a Kiwi batter against England. 463 runs till now.
On a length and outside off, Tim Southee steers it towards the off side but finds the fielder at point.
Jamie Overton starts with a good-length delivery on middle. Daryl Mitchell works it towards deep square leg for a single.

FOUR! Straight back over the keeper! England going with the short ball strategy for Tim Southee who is prepared. He makes room and swings his bat, gets a thick top edge that flies over Ben Foakes for a boundary!

FOUR! Two in a row! A much better shot from Tim Southee and he has decided to attack. Jamie Overton bangs this in but does not rise as much as expected. Tim Southee makes room and thumps it through covers for another boundary!
Short again but follows Tim Southee as he tries to make room. Manages to roll his wrists and work it towards mid-wicket for a single.

FOUR! Daryl Mitchell gets involved this time! Jamie Overton goes short to Daryl Mitchell as well but he just stands tall and dismisses it towards the deep square boundary for the third four of the over.
Good-length delivery this time on off stump. Daryl Mitchell stands tall to defend and then almost tries to catch the ball as it bounces off the pitch. Good decision to leave that one alone!
Bowls it on leg, Tim Southee flicks it towards leg gully and scampers for a quick one. This is good running between the wickets.
Bowls it on middle this time, Daryl Mitchell defends it back towards the bowler.

SIX! What a way to get to his hundred. What a series Daryl Mitchell is having! On a length and on middle, Daryl Mitchell uses his feet and lofts it over the long off fence for a biggie. Daryl Mitchell becomes the first New Zealand batter to get three successive centuries against England. His 4th Test hundred overall.
Full on leg stump. Daryl Mitchell defends this back down the pitch.
Full once again on middle. Daryl Mitchell defends towards the onside.
Fired into the pads, Daryl Mitchell doesn't get bat to it and works it leg side for a single.
Full outside off, Daryl Mitchell defends this towards Jamie Overton.

FOUR! Daryl Mitchell seems to be ready to attack England now that he has reached his century! Full toss on middle and Daryl Mitchell punches this straight to the long on boundary. Holds his elbows high and keeps the pose for a while. Commanding display from Daryl Mitchell!
Slightly back of a length on middle. Daryl Mitchell works it to square leg for a single.

FOUR! Tim Southee doing well dealing with these short balls! Jamie Overton is not getting these shot balls right, Tim Southee swings and gets the toe end of the bat, as the ball races towards the mid-wicket boundary! Ben Stokes can not get across to stop the ball.
Short once again, Tim Southee swings and misses this time.

FOUR! Three boundaries in an over once again! Jamie Overton goes full this time and attempts a yorker. Tim Southee expects the bowler to go full at some point puts his bat down in time and works it towards point for a boundary! Tim Southee is playing a crucial knock here!
Tossed up delivery on leg, Daryl Mitchell works it towards short mid-wicket fielder.
Bowls it outside leg, Daryl Mitchell looks to flick it but misses. A loud shout for caught behind but the finger stays down. Stokes asks Leach but they end up not reviewing it.
This is outside leg, Daryl Mitchell looks to sweep it but misses. The ball races from the keeper's leg and towards fine leg where the fielder makes a diving stop. Couple taken.
Outside leg, Daryl Mitchell blocks it with his pads.
Tosses it up around off, Mitchell defends it back to the bowler.
Short of a length here from Jack Leach, Mitchell nudges it behind square for a single
Good-length delivery on leg stump, Worked to mid-wicket for a single.
Back of a length this time on off, Tim Southee makes room and gets the thick edge towards a very fine third man for a single.
Full and angling into the pads. The field is back for Daryl Mitchell and gets an easy single towards mid-wicket.
Short once again to Tim Southee, going down leg side. The batter ducks under this one.
Back-of-a-length delivery angled into the body, Tim Southee gets up and gets an inside edge onto himself.
Short on leg stump. Tim Southee pulls this to backward square leg for a single.
Tossed up on middle, Tim Southee blocks it back towards the bowler.
Similar to the last delivery, this is again defended towards the bowler.
On middle again, Tim Southee defends it towards the mid on fielder.
Goes outside off this time, Tim Southee guides it towards the fielder at gully.

OUT! CAUGHT! What a catch from the skipper, Stokes. Lands it fuller and on off, Daryl Mitchell lofts it over mid off but doesn't get the power right. Ben Stokes chases it over his shoulders and reverse cups it to his left. A fine catch from Stokes and it ends an excellent innings from Daryl Mitchell. That will be LUNCH on Day 2.
Howout: c Ben Stokes b Jack Leach

Commentary: Tossed up, on off. Southee blocks it out on the front foot.
On a length and angling across. Wagner looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length and around middle. Wagner punches it to mid on.
Short of a length and around middle. Wagner stays back and punches it again to mid on.
This is full and outside off, shaping away. Wagner looks to drive but misses it completely.
FOUR! Beautiful shot from Wagner and he is off the mark! On a length and outside off. Wagner punches off the back foot through mid off. Stokes gives a chase but to no avail as the ball wins the race.
Length and outside off, hit straight to mid off.

OUT! TAKEN! Leach has another one! Leach tosses it up, full and around off. Southee clears his front leg and tries to go over mid off but fails to make a proper connection and the ball balloons up and Ben Stokes settles himself to take the catch. Southee goes after playing a crucial cameo.
Howout: c Ben Stokes b Jack Leach

Commentary: Length and on off. Wagner goes back and blocks it.

OUT! CAUGHT! Jack Leach finishes with a five-fer! Leach tosses it up again, full and around middle and off. Wagner heaves it away to deep mid-wicket. Jonny Bairstow was late to react as he runs across from long on but rushes and takes a superb tumbling catch to his left. Just ten deliveries after Lunch for England to bundle the visitors out. New Zealand are all out on 329.
Howout: c Jonny Bairstow b Jack Leach

Commentary: Length and down the leg side. Lees leaves it alone.

DROPPED! Chance early on for New Zealand but fail to take it! Short of a length and outside off, there is extra bounce and pace. Lees looks to cut hard but gets an outside edge to first slip where Daryl Mitchell leaps and tries to take over his head but fumbles. It rolls behind off his hand for a boundary.
Length ball, outside off. Lees lets it through.
BEATEN! On a length and just outside off. Lees defends the wrong line and gets beaten on the outside edge.

OUT! TIMBER! What a beauty from Trent Boult! That is just superb and the crowd is stunned! A length ball, around middle, it lands and jags away. Lees keeps his head down as he looks to defend but the ball swings away and beats the outside edge before rattling the top of off. What a start for New Zealand! Daryl Mitchell will be a happy man right now!
Howout: b Trent Boult

Commentary: Length ball, going away from the batter. Pope shoulders arms to it.
A length ball, around the 5th stump channel, hint of away swing. Crawley shoulders arms.

FOUR! Crawley is off the mark in a streaky way! This is full and on off, swings away slightly. Crawley looks to work on the leg side and gets a leading edge, straight down and it races into the fence.
Length and on off. Defended.
Length ball, outside off, swinging away. Left alone.
This one is again outside off. Left by Zak.
Too straight on middle, Crawley eases it to mid on.
A length ball, shaping into the batter. Pope tucks it behind square leg for a single. He is off the mark.
Tries to swing back in but fails and serves it way outside off. Crawley lets it go.
Tight this time but again it is outside off. Crawley shoulders arms to it.
Leg bye! Length ball, on the pads. Crawley fails to tuck it away and gets hit on the pads. It rolls to square leg for a leg bye.
FOUR! Well played! Touch fuller and swinging in around middle. Pope stays back and flicks it past square leg for a boundary.
Short of a length and on middle, nudged to square leg.
A length ball, outside off, moving away. Crawley shoulders arms to it.
A length ball, around off, slanting in. Crawley guides it to point. Not in the gap.
BEAUTY! A full ball from wide of the crease and angling around off. It draws Crawley to play at it but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Tad fuller and on off, pushed to covers.
Length and outside off. Left alone.
Slants one around the off stump channel. Crawley gets a straight bat down to defend it.
This is discipline bowling from Boult! He is making the ball swing back in, just around off. Pope is like a rock on his defense though.
This one goes with the angle outside off. Pope lets it through to the keeper.
Very full and there is late in-swing as well, this is outside off. Pope steps across and looks to drive but gets an inside edge onto the pads.

OUT! BOWLED! This is high-class bowling from Trent Boult! A genius at work! Ollie Pope was struggling in this over to play Boult and he fails to play here! A fuller ball, lands across around off and swings back in sharply. Ollie Pope is squared up as he plays all over it. He tries to work on the leg side but misses and the ball goes through the gate and the off-stump is uprooted. Boult is pumped up and why wouldn't he be!
Howout: b Trent Boult

Commentary: Full and on middle, Root drives it to mid on.
A length ball, outside off, no swing this time and Root leaves it alone.
Fuller and on the pads. Crawley fails to flick it away and gets hit on the pads.
Full ball, around off. Crawley makes a solid block.

A direct-hit and Root was surely gone! Length and outside off. Crawley taps it to the left of mid off and calls for a quick single. Root was late to reach but rushes across and almost gave up in the end. Kane Williamson has a shy at the keeper's end but misses.
Length and down the leg side. Left alone.
Slants it on the pads, it is flicked to deep square leg for a single.
Full, straight on the pads again, Crawley nudged to deep mid-wicket for a single.
A full ball, angling across, outside off. Crawley makes an easy leave
This one is at 138 kph, on off. Blocked to covers.
Boult tries to shape back in but fails and this one goes with the angle, outside off. Crawley lets it through.
Full and outside off, there is late away swing and Crawley makes another leave.

OUT! BOWLED! WOW! What a delivery! Yet again Boult gets the ball to move and Crawley knew the moment he missed there, that he has to make the long walk! Boult steams in and serves a fuller ball, around middle and off, it lands and swings back in. Zak Crawley without any movement looks to drive it straight but leaves a big gap between the bat and pad and the ball makes his way to touch the stumps behind. This is excellent stuff from the left-arm Kiwi bowler.
Howout: b Trent Boult

Commentary: A wicket-maiden for Boult! Length ball, angling aross and Bairstow shoulders arms to it.
FOUR! Fuller and angling on off, hint of swing there. Root is squared up as he looks to defend and gets a thick outside edge, over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
Length ball, shaping away, outside off. Root watchfully leaves it.
An out-swinger, fuller and outside off. Joe lets it through to the keeper.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Southee gets his first and it's the dangerous wicket of Root this time! New Zealand well and truly on top! Southee keeps on bowling wide outside off but he serves a fuller ball, angling around the 5th stump channel. Root hangs back to push but does so inside the line and manages to get an outside edge to Tom Blundell who pouches it. England in early trouble as they lose their fourth wicket.
Howout: c Tom Blundell b Tim Southee

Commentary: Stokes is already busy on the crease! Full and on off. Stokes skips down and drives it through covers to get off the mark with a couple of runs.
Fuller and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
A bumper, for the first time in quite a while and Bairstow sits under it.
Length and outside off, punched to covers.
On middle, blocked out.
FOUR! Bairstow is off the mark! This is full and wide outside off. Bairstow leans and drives it through covers for a boundary.
FOUR! Two in a row! Wide from Boult again, fuller and Bairstow drives it through covers for another boundary.
Around the wicket on a good length, angled in from outside off. Ben Stokes defends towards mid on.
SIX! Ben Stokes has decided to counter attack! Good-length delivery on off stump turned full by Ben Stokes as he gives it the charge. Thumps it over long off for a biggie! We are in for a ride!
Great comeback from Tim Southee. Bowls on a good length just outside off, swings away from the Ben Stokes who plays at it and is beaten.
On a good length outside off. Ben Stokes takes a stride forward and defends to covers.
Good-length delivery on leg. Ben Stokes shuffles forward and flicks it to deep square leg for a single.

FOUR! Could have been the fifth wicket for New Zealand! Not quite short enough outside off, Jonny Bairstow slashes hard at it and just manages to lift it over the slip cordon for a boundary to third man! Jonny Bairstow gets lucky there!
Good-length delivery on off, Defended towards point.
Middle stump line on a good length. Ben Stokes fends it towards mid on.
FOUR! That has been dispatched! Slightly back of a length outside off, Ben Stokes gives it the charge and slashes it towards backward point for a four! That reached the boundary in no time!

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Ben Stokes! This one caressed through cover-point for a beautiful boundary! Trent Boult goes slightly full outside off stump, Ben Stokes opens the face of the bat and times it wonderfully!
Full on the pads, Ben Stokes flicks it towards mid-wicket and gets a quick single.

FOUR! Third boundary of the over! This one was fortunate! Back-of-a-length delivery outside off, Jonny Bairstow tries to cut but gets a massive bottom edge past the stumps and Tom Blundell who is left wrong footed. Runs to the fine leg boundary to get England moving forward!
Ben Stokes charges Neil Wagner on his first ball! Around the wicket on a good length outside off, shapes away and beats Ben Stokes.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ben Stokes cameo comes to an end! Neil Wagner has broken this counter attacking partnership! Stokes gives the bowler the charge once again who bowls a full slower delivery on off. The shot is mistimed straight to mid off where Kane Williamson is placed perfectly for the catch!
Howout: c Kane Williamson b Neil Wagner

Commentary: Bowls it on a length and on off, Ben Foakes defends it towards mid off fielder.
On a length outside off, left alone by Ben Foakes.

OUT! LBW! Ben Foakes goes upstairs after been given LBW but the decision is upheld. On a length and on middle, Ben Foakes looks to block it but misses as the ball hits his pads. A loud appeal and the finger goes up. Foakes take a review. Ball Tracking shows three reds and he has to walk away. Big trouble for England. They are crumbling here at 6 down for 55.
Howout: lbw b Neil Wagner

Commentary: Huge appeal once again! The umpire does not raise his finger this time and New Zealand review! Pitching outside leg shows Ball Tracker, and the umpire's decision stands. Slightly full and swinging in, hits Jamie Overton hard on his pads. New Zealand lose a review.
Bowls it on a length and on middle, Jonny Bairstow defends it away.
Short delivery on leg, Jonny Bairstow guides it towards backward point for a single.
Short delivery on leg, Jonny Bairstow pulls it towards backward square leg for a single.
Good-length delivery on middle. Worked towards backward square leg once again for an easy single.
Fuller this time outside off, Knocks it towards covers.
FOUR! First boundary for the debutant in Test cricket! Full once again outside off, Jamie Overton strides forward and crunches it through the vacant cover region for a boundary!
Full and outside off, tempting Jonny Bairstow to drive. Neil Wagner nearly succeeds as Jonny Bairstow goes for it and gets beaten.
Full delivery outside off. Jonny Bairstow pushes it towards mid off.
Full and angling away from the right-handed batter, Jonny Bairstow leaves it alone.
Slightly short and outside off, Jonny Bairstow gets low and cuts it towards backward point for a single.
Really full outside off. Jamie Overton times it well straight to the point fielder.
