Full once again and swinging in from middle. Thumps against the pads of Jamie Overton and there is an appeal from the bowler! Umpire reckons it's going down leg and so does the bowler. There is no review taken and that is a massive mistake as replays have just shown that it would have been all three reds! Another review opportunity missed in this Test match! Hopefully it does not prove to be as decisive as the one England missed! Two wickets in the over and should have been three! Great first over from Neil Wagner!
Goes fuller and outside off, Jonny Bairstow drives it towards short cover and straight towards the fielder.
On leg this time, Jonny Bairstow flicks it towards the leg side for a quick single.
Lands it on a length and down the middle, Jamie Overton defends it solidly off the front foot.
Much fuller and on off, Jamie Overton blocks it away on the off side.
Good-length delivery on off, Jamie Overton eases it towards short cover and scampers for a quick single.
FOUR! Slightly shorter and on middle, Jonny Bairstow pulls this one towards backward square leg for a boundary.

Jamie Overton gets a lucky escape. This lands on a length and outside off, Jamie Overton looks to drive it but gets a thick inside edge and the ball rolls past the stumps and towards fine leg. They take a couple of runs.
FOUR! This is perfectly timed. Outside off this time, Jamie Overton plays a cover drive as the ball races the deep extra cover fence.
On off, defended out.
Fuller and wide outside off, Jamie Overton drives it through the cover. Good fielding from the fielder who half stops it and restricts it to a single.
Outside off again, Jonny Bairstow drives it towards covers for a brace.
On middle, this is defended towards the leg side.
On a length and outside off, Jamie Overton eases it towards the short cover fielder.
Lands it on a length and outside off, Jamie Overton guides it towards the mid off fielder.
Fires it down the middle, Jamie Overton defends it towards the mid on region.

This is much fuller and outside off, Jamie Overton looks to drive it but misses. A loud appeal and the finger goes up. Jamie Overton takes a review. Ultra Edge shows no spike and the decision is reversed. He survives.

Good-length delivery angled down leg. Jamie Overton tries to work this leg side but misses the ball. Tim Southee appeals loudly for an LBW decision but the umpire walks away as the batters run for a leg bye.
On a good length once again outside off, Jonny Bairstow gets forward and defends it towards mid off.
Bowls it fuller and outside leg, Jamie Overton looks to flick it but the ball brushes his pads and rolls towards short fine leg. Leg bye taken.
This is wide outside off, Jonny Bairstow steers it towards point and takes one.
Shorter and on middle, Jamie Overton looks to pull it but misses as the ball goes towards the keeper.
Fuller and wide of off-stump, Overton drives it to mid-off for a single.
Dropped! A slower ball on middle, Bairstow checks his shot as the ball lobs back to Wagner who drops it at the follow-through. A tough chance here and Jonny Bairstow gets a lucky escape.
Shorter and outside off, Jonny Bairstow cuts it but finds the fielder at backward point. They take a single.
On off, this is defended towards point fielder.
Good-length delivery on middle. Jonny Bairstow works it towards square leg for a single.
Middle stump line on a good length, Jamie Overton works it backward of square leg for a single.
Great length from Tim Southee, consistent bowling outside off. Jonny Bairstow lunges forward and defends towards the offside.
Tim Southee bowls on a good length once again just outside off. Solid defense from Jonny Bairstow.
Strays in line and bowls down leg this time on a good length, Jonny Bairstow works this to fine leg for one.
Bowls it on a length and outside leg, Jonny Bairstow gives it a fine tickle as the ball rolls towards short fine leg. They rotate the strike.
This is outside off, Jamie Overton looks to drive it but gets a thick inside edge as the ball races towards fine leg. Single taken.
Bowls it outside off, left alone by Jonny Bairstow.
This was close. Fuller and on stumps, Jonny Bairstow looks to flick it but gets a thick inside edge as the ball rolls towards the leg side. They take a single.
This one lands outside leg, Jamie Overton looks to flick it but the ball brushes his pads and rolls towards the leg side. Leg bye taken.
This is fuller and on leg, Jonny Bairstow flicks it towards square leg for one. That will be Tea on Day 2.
A full ball on off, bit of away shape. Bairstow defends it to covers.
Length ball, outside off, straight this time. Bairstow has a poke at it but misses.
A length ball, outside off. Bairstow leaves it alone.
Away swing there but the line is outside off. Bairstow lets it go.
Southee keeps bowling in the outside off channel and Bairstow is happy to leave it alone.
Full, outside off, swinging in. Bairstow drives it to deep point and will keep the strike for the next over.
A full ball, around off, shaping in. Bairstow is right behind the line of the ball to block it.
Short of a length and on off. Bairstow pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Length and on the pads. Overton stays back to keep it out.
On a length and on off. Overton solidly blocks it.

A length ball, around middle and it swings back in sharply, extra bounce as well. Overton looks to flick but misses and gets rapped on the pads. A huge appeal for LBW but looks like there is an inside edge. Boult though convinces Kane Williamson to take the review. Ultra Edge shows nothing on it and Ball Tracking shows the ball goes onto miss the stumps. Not out it is. New Zealand lost the review.
On middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
This is full and outside off. Bairstow drives it to the right of deep point and the batters get a couple of runs.
FOUR! Good shot! Too full and outside off. Bairstow gets on the front foot and drives it through the diving cover fielder for a boundary. 5000 Test runs for Jonny Bairstow.
This one nips back in, on a length and on middle. Bairstow hangs back to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Full and outside off. Bairstow square drives it to point where the man runs to his right and cuts it. Two runs. 100 up as well for England.
Tight leave! On a length and comes with the angle around off. Bairstow shoulders arms.
Length ball, outside off. Overton mistimes his punch on the off side.
Too full on this occasion, on off, pushed to covers.
FOUR! The stand now crosses the 50-run mark! Full again, on middle. Overton drives it straight past mid off for a boundary.
On a length and outside off. Overton cuts it late and past the gully region for a couple of runs.
Full ball from around the wicket and on middle. Blocked out.
Keeps the same angle and serves it on the pads, it is pulled to deep mid-wicket for a couple.
Length and outside off. Bairstow drops it to point for an easy single.
Outside off, blocked out.
FOUR! A full ball, outside off, late outswing there. Overton leans to drive but gets an outside edge and it flies uppishly in the gully region for a boundary.
Outside off on a length. Overton shoulders arms.
Good delivery! A length ball, outside off and it nips back in sharply. Overton tries to defend away from the body and gets beaten on the inside edge.
On middle, nudged past mid-wicket for one more.
Length and on top of off. Overton knocks it to covers.
A length ball, on off. Overton defends with hard hands and gets a thick inside edge to square leg.
Around off, worked to cover-point.
A well-targeted inswinger, on middle. Overton gets a straight bat down and pushes to mid on.
A length ball, outside off, this one holds its line. Overton looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge. That was close.
BEATEN AGAIN! Length ball, outside off, again holds its line. Overton looks to block it towards mid off but fails to get any bat on it.
FOUR! Two away from fifty now, Bairstow! A length ball, outside off. Bairstow opens the face of the bat and plays it to third man for a boundary.

FOUR! Fifty for Jonny Bairstow! His 23rd Test fifty! Length and outside off. Bairstow cuts it late and to third man for another boundary. He came at a very difficult time but has done brilliantly to get things under control.
On middle, worked to deep square leg for a single.
This is outside off. Overton dabs it to backward point.
On off, kept out.
A full ball, outside off. Jamie shoulders arms.
A length ball, outside off, across the right-hander and Bairstow looks to push but misses.
On a length and on off. Bairstow steers it to deep backward point for a single. They were looking for a couple but the fielder is quick to collect.
A length ball, across outside off. Overton looks to defend but misses. Overton is struggling against Boult!
An inswinger, fuller and on middle, driven straight to mid off.
Beaten! A length ball, outside off, across the angle and Overton swings and misses.
'Round the wicket! Fuller and on off. Overton is solid in his defense.
Length ball, outside off. Bairstow crunches it to sweeper cover who runs to his right and stops it. Two runs.
Angles it down the leg side. Bairstow misses his flick. Blundell does well to get his mitts on it.
On a length and around middle and leg. Bairstow fails to tuck it away and gets hit on the pads. Was sliding down.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Overpitched around off. Bairstow punches it down the ground, wide of mid on for a boundary.
Bairstow drives it again but this time straight and Southee gets a hand to it.
Outside off, on a length. Bairstow punches it to point.
FOUR! Greets Michael Bracewell with a boundary! Tossed up, quicker and on middle. Overton steps down and across and sweeps it fine to fine leg for a boundary.
Flatter, slower and outside off, punched to covers.
On middle, Overton waits on the back foot as he tucks it to square leg for a run.
Flatter, slower and just around off, it stays low as well. Bairstow opens his body up and looks to pull but misses. The ball whizzes past the off pole.
Play and a miss again! A loopy ball, outside off, not much pace again. Bairstow steps across and looks to sweep but misses.
Slightly shorter and on off. Bairstow waits on the back foot and fends it to square leg for a single.
FOUR! Jonny Bairstow looks in sublime touch! Neil Wagner starts with a short delivery outside off stump. Jonny Bairstow does not miss out as he places the ball past backward point for a boundary!
Fuller this time swing in from middle. Jonny Bairstow gets his bat down in time and fends it towards mid on.
Similar delivery just a little fuller, Jonny Bairstow gets behind this one well and punches it to mid on.
Pulls his length back outside off, Jonny Bairstow gets a single towards point.
Full and angling down the pads, Jamie Overton works it towards fine leg for a single.
Full and wide, thumped towards covers.
Tossed up on middle, Jamie Overton guides it towards mid on and straight towards the fielder.
Flighted up on middle, Jamie Overton flicks it towards square leg for one.
FOUR! On a length and on middle, Jonny Bairstow pulls it hard and through the deep square leg fence for a boundary.
Low full toss outside off, worked wide of long off for two runs!
Flighted on a good length outside off, Jonny Bairstow sweeps towards deep square leg for a single.

SIX! That's the 100-run partnership between these two and Jamie Overton brings it up in style! Charges the bowler and catches the ball on the full and clobbers it over long on for the maximum. First six for Jamie Overton in Test cricket!

FOUR! Jonny Bairstow is striking at over 100 and is looking dangerous! Full delivery pitching on leg, Jonny Bairstow moves his leg out of the way and powers it towards mid-wicket for a boundary! Brute strength from Jonny!
Shorter this angled into the body, Jonny Bairstow pulls it to backward square leg for a single.
Inswinger on a good length, pitching on leg, Jamie Overton does not connect and Neil Wagner makes an optimistic appeal. Maybe an inside edge as well.
Full on middle, defended towards mid on.
Good-length delivery on off stump. Fended towards the offside.
Full and outside off, Jamie Overton lets this one through to the keeper.
Tossed up on middle with a hint of turn, Jonny Bairstow flicks it towards leg gully and scampers for a quick one.

Not out! Tossed up outside off, Jamie Overton looks to sweep it but misses. The ball goes into the hands of the keeper who is quick enough to whip the bails off. The decision is taken upstairs. Replay shows that Jamie Overton was well inside his crease. Not out.
Good-length delivery outside off, keeps its line and Jamie Overton leaves it alone.
FOUR! Too short from Michael Bracewell! Bowls this wide outside off and Jamie Overton has room to free his arms and muscle it through covers for a boundary!
Short once again but a little closer to the stumps. Jamie Overton takes a step back a cuts it past backward point for three runs. He moves to 49 now.
Full and outside off, Jonny Bairstow get across towards the offside and sweeps this towards backward square leg for a single.
Short and angling away from the batter, Jonny Bairstow goes for a pull and gets an inside edge down onto the pitch.

Great bowling from Neil Wagner! The field was set for a short delivery but bowls a full slower delivery outside off stump. Jonny Bairstow is not prepared for that and puts his bat to it. Just manages to lob it over the mid on fielder who dives back but is out of reach. They collect three runs.

FOUR! Jamie Overton is making New Zealand pay for not taking that review! That is fifty on debut for Jamie Overton as he gets there in style. Short delivery pitching on leg and is dispatched towards the mid-wicket boundary!
Short once again into the body. Jamie Overton gets on his toes and plays it down with soft hands.
That's thumped the batter on the helmet! Short delivery once again and Jamie Overton pulls but gets an outside edge onto his helmet!

FOUR! It is all going England's way at the moment! Short and outside off stump, Jamie Overton makes room and slashes hard at the ball but only manages a thick edge that takes it high between the keeper and second slip for a streaky boundary! 11 runs off this over!
Tossed up delivery, Jonny Bairstow uses his feet and works it straight towards the mid-wicket fielder.
FOUR! Fuller in length and on middle, Jonny Bairstow gets on his knees and slog sweeps it through backward square leg for a boundary. This was a perfectly timed shot from Jonny Bairstow.
Outside off this time, Jonny Bairstow steers it towards backward point for one.
Bowls it on middle, Jamie Overton defends it towards the leg side.
Goes outside off again, Jamie Overton cuts it towards backward point. Neil Wagner with a long chase and just saves it before the fence. Three runs taken.
Outside off with a hint of turn, Jonny Bairstow looks to sweep it but misses.
Shorter and on middle, Jamie Overton looks to pull it but misses. The ball hits his chest and rolls towards the off side.
Outside leg this time, Jamie Overton looks to play at it but misses.
SIX! Brilliant from Jamie Overton. Shorter and on off, Jamie Overton smashes it hard and over the cow corner fence for a biggie. He moves to 66.
FOUR! Sublime. Fuller and outside off, Jamie Overton drives it straight down the ground and towards the long off fence for a boundary.
Bowls it on off, this is defended out solidly.
FOUR! Shorter and outside off, Jamie Overton hits it hard and over covers for a two-bounce boundary.
Bowls it outside off and on a length, Jonny Bairstow defends it towards the off side.
On a length and outside off, Jonny Bairstow cuts it towards backward point for one. This brings 150-run partnership for Jonny Bairstow and Jamie Overton.

Bowls it on a length and on off, Jamie Overton looks to defend it but gets an inside edge and hits the pads. Daryl Mitchell thinks it had hit straight on the pads and shouts out loud but the umpire was uninterested.
On off, kept out.
Lands it on a length and outside off, Jamie Overton leaves it alone.
FOUR! Fuller and outside off, Jamie Overton looks to drive it but gets a thick outside edge as the ball races towards the third man fence for a boundary.
Goes fuller and on the stumps, Jonny Bairstow flicks it towards square leg for one.
Fuller in length and outside off, Jamie Overton guides it towards the fielder at mid off.
Outside off from Tim Southee, solid block from Jamie Overton.
Bowls it outside off again, Jamie Overton shoulders arms at it.
On a good length and down the middle, Jamie Overton defends it towards the vacant short leg region.
Bowls it outside leg this time, Jamie Overton looks to flick it but misses.
Slightly shorter and outswinger from Daryl Mitchell, Jonny Bairstow looks to defend it but misses.
Bowls it outside off again, Jonny Bairstow tries to drive it but misses again.
Sticks to bowling it outside off, Jonny Bairstow eases it towards the mid off fielder.
Sticks to his line and length, Jonny Bairstow gets in two minds but leaves it alone in the end.
Bowls it on leg this time, Jonny Bairstow flicks it towards square leg fielder.
Touch fuller and outside off, Jonny Bairstow drives it hard and through covers. Michael Bracewell does well at the deep cover fence. A couple of runs taken.
Good-length delivery on off, Jamie Overton defends this back to the bowler.
Slightly full outside off, Jamie Overton steps across the stumps and works it towards deep square leg for a single.
Tim Southee bowls this short and wide from the off stump, Jonny Bairstow places it towards deep point and takes a single.
Full outswinger outside off, Jamie Overton takes a stride and works it in the cover-point direction for a brace.
On a good length this time attacking the stumps, Jamie Overton defends towards mid on.
Outside off on a good length, Jamie Overton knocks this to the cover fielder.
FOUR! Gorgeous on-drive! Daryl Mitchell goes full on middle. Jonny Bairstow punches this straight past the bowler to go one hit away from another century!
Lands it outside off, Jonny Bairstow cuts it towards backward point.
Full angling down leg stump, Jonny Bairstow flicks this towards deep square leg and looks for two. In the end they settle for one.

FOUR! This has been dismissed from sight! Length ball on off, Jamie Overton makes room and plunders this straight back past the bowler. The umpire takes evasive action and for good reason! That one was hit hard!
Full on middle, defended back to the bowler.
Good-length delivery, shaping away from outside off, Jamie Overton leaves this one alone.

FOUR! Back-to-back centuries for Jonny Bairstow! He has got there in quick time and has saved England from a very difficult position! Full outside off stump, Jonny Bairstow takes a couple of steps forward and places it past the diving mid off player for a boundary to bring up a memorable century! He removes his helmet and punches the air and celebrates what has been an exhibition of stroke play!
Lands it on a length and outside off, Jonny Bairstow blocks it towards the mid off fielder.
FOUR! Length and outside off again, Jonny Bairstow uses the pace of the ball and cuts it through slips. The ball races towards third man for a boundary.
Touch fuller and outside off, Jonny Bairstow looks to loft it but misses. The ball just aired past his bat and towards the keeper.
Fuller in length and outside off, Jonny Bairstow defends it towards the off side.
Goes outside leg this time, Jonny Bairstow looks to give it a fine tickle but misses. The keeper misses it as well. Two leg byes taken.
Edged! that was close. Lower ball outside off, Jamie Overton looks to play at it but gets an inside edge. The ball just falls short of the keeper.
Full outside off, powered towards deep cover-point for a single.
FOUR! Short ball and gets the treatment!  Tim Southee does not get enough in the bouncer and Jonny Bairstow is in the firm of his life. Pulls this wide of fine leg for another boundary!
Back-of-a-length delivery outside off, Jonny Bairstow reaches for it and slashes but does not connect.
FOUR! Second of the over for Jonny Bairstow! Full and wide asking to be hit, Jonny Bairstow obliges and hits this past the diving cover fielder for four more runs!
Short once again but cramps Jonny Bairstow for room as he mistimes it towards cover.
On a length and on off, Jamie Overton guides it towards gully and scampers for a quick single.
Bowls it on middle, Jonny Bairstow defends it solidly. Jamie Overton wanted a single but was sent back.
Outside off this time, Jonny Bairstow cuts it to point for a brace.
On a length and down the middle, Jonny Bairstow eases it back towards Trent Boult.
Goes outside off this time, Jonny Bairstow looks to play at it but misses.
Shorter and down the leg side, Jonny Bairstow ducks underneath it.
Outswinger outside off, on a good length. Jamie Overton hits this to deep cover-point for a single.

FOUR! A mis-hit gives Jonny Bairstow a boundary! Full delivery on middle, Jonny Bairstow tries to loft it over long on but doesnt get good timing on that. Just about beats the mid on fielder and trickles across the ropes for four runs!
Slightly full outside off, knocked towards cover.
On a good length and outside off, Jonny Bairstow plays at it and misses.
Slower delivery on a good length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow taps it gently towards cover.
Good-length delivery on off, Jonny Bairstow gets across and taps it onside.
Touch fuller and outside leg, Jamie Overton looks to flick it but the ball hits his pads and rolls towards the leg side. Leg bye taken.
On a good length and down the middle, Jonny Bairstow blocks it off the front foot.
Bowls it on middle again, Jonny Bairstow hits it straight but finds the fielder at mid on.
FOUR! On off and on a good length, Jonny Bairstow waits for the ball and cuts it towards fine leg for a boundary. This brings up 200 partnership for Jonny Bairstow and Jamie Overton.
On off, kept out.
FOUR! Shorter and on leg, Jonny Bairstow pulls it hard but miscues it towards fine leg. He gets a boundary anyways.
Goes outside off this time, Jamie Overton looks to play at it but misses.
Fuller and down the middle, Jamie Overton flicks it towards mid-wicket for one.
Bowls it outside off, Jonny Bairstow guides it towards the off side for a single.
On a length and on leg, Jamie Overton defends it towards the fielder at short cover.
Touch fuller and on middle, this is flicked towards the leg side.
Fuller one again, Jamie Overton defends it towards the short cover fielder.
Goes outside off angling it into the batter, Jonny Bairstow looks to defend it but misses.
Outside off and much fuller in length, Jonny Bairstow eases it towards the mid off fielder.
Bowls it outside off again, Jonny Bairstow defends it towards the fielder at short cover.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Jonny Bairstow shoulders arms at it and lets it go.
This one lands fuller and down the middle, Jonny Bairstow flicks it towards the fielder at leg gully.
Fuller again and on leg, Jonny Bairstow clips it towards deep square leg for one. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 2.
Floated and full, on off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it on the front foot.
This time it is full again, on leg. Bairstow nudges it to the leg side.
First run of the day and the crowd cheers. Full and on the pads. Jonny Bairstow tucks it through square leg for a single.
Quicker and full, at the stumps. Jamie Overton blocks it out solidly.
Touch flatter, on the pads. Jamie Overton flicks it to square leg and gets across for a single. He moves to 90.
On middle and leg, flicked towards mid on. A tidy start by Michael Bracewell.
Some movement to start with! Good-length delivery, outside off, shaping away a touch. Jamie Overton looks to chase it but misses.
This is touch fuller, on the fifth stump. Overton defends it solidly on the front foot.
A length ball, around off, Overton blocks it to covers.
Too straight! On a length, on the pads, could not get the movement in play. Jamie Overton stays back and clips it deep square leg for a single. Headingley is cheering every run here.
Good running! Length ball, on middle and leg. Jonny Bairstow tucks it through square leg and comes back for the second run.

THAT IS CLOSE! This one lands outside off and nips back in sharply. Jonny Bairstow trusts his judgement and leaves it alone. Although, it was not far away from the off pole. A good end to the over by Southee.

Trent Boult starts on a good note, he finds the outside edge but this one does not carry. It is on a length, on off. Jamie Overton tries to defend it out but it goes towards gully off the outside edge, but meets the fielder on a bounce.
Tempting but unplayable! It is much fuller this time, angled across the right-hander on off. Jamie Overton leaves it alone.
Much straighter this time. On a length, on leg. Overton flicks it to the leg side but not in the gap.
Boult serves it on a length, on top of off. Overton defends it out.
BEATEN! Full length, outside off, this shapes away with the angle. Jamie Overton gets beaten on the outside edge.
A maiden over for Boult. He starts from where he left off. Good length, on off. Overton fends it out to point.
Full length, on off. Jonny Bairstow nudges it to mid on and scampers across for a single.
A length delivery this time, at 133 kph, with some extra bounce off the deck. Jamie Overton uses the depth of his crease and defends it out.
Good length, outside off. Jamie Overton lets it through to the keeper.
Swing and a miss! Faction short, wide outside off. Jamie Overton throws his blade at it but gets beaten by the pace and extra bounce.
Southee goes full, around middle and leg. Jamie Overton flicks it to the leg side. Four dots in a row now.
Make that 5. Jamie Overton blocks this full-length delivery to mid on.
A sharp bouncer, on middle. Jonny Bairstow ducks under it. Although the umpire signals it as a wide due to height.
FOUR! Jonny Bairstow gets the first boundary of the day. It is short and outside off. Jonny Bairstow gets on his front foot and punches it through covers for a boundary.
Length ball, on the pads, Jonny Bairstow clips it to fine leg for a couple.
Length, on off, defended out.
Touch fuller, on off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it out watchfully.
It is on a length, around off. Jonny Bairstow taps it to covers and gets across.
Swing and a miss! A good end to the over by Boult. This is on a length, wide outside off. Jamie Overton looks to chase it but only manages to connect with thin air.
Full length, on off. Jonny Bairstow defends it to backward point.
Good length, around off. Jonny Bairstow pushes it to cover for a single.

Jamie Overton has to put in a dive to get home! A length ball, on off. Overton stays back and punches it down to long off. Kane Williamson charges towards the ball and has a shy at the non-striker's end but misses. They cross for a single.
This one comes back a touch. Full, on middle and leg. Jonny Bairstow tucks it to mid on.
FOUR! Clever placement! On a length, around the pads. Jonny Bairstow stays back and flicks it past mid on, into the gap and into the boundary. Incredible shot.
Touch short, on off. Jonny Bairstow punches it through covers and gets a couple. He moves to 148.
Full length, on off. Jamie Overton defends it out solidly.

Boult continues to remain full, but this time attack the leg stump. Jamie Overton nurdles it to mid on. Somebody is wondering around in the Hospitality Box. Not the first time this morning. Jamie Overton is clearly frustrated.
Swing and a miss! On a length, outside off, shaping away from the right-hander. Jamie Overton tries to expand his hands for a drive but misses.
Beaten again! Fraction short, outside off. Jamie Overton tries to heave it across the line but only connects with thin air. He is in his nervy 90s.
Connects well, but finds the fielder. Full length, on fourth stump. Overton leans in and drives it to covers. The fielder dives to his left and stops the ball.
FOUR! This should release some pressure off him. Full-length ball, wide outside off. Jamie Overton creams it through covers for a fine boundary. He moves to 96.

WOW! 150 for Jonny Bairstow. This is the second fastest by an English player. Headingley is on its feet. Full length, on off. Jonny Bairstow drives it through the gap at covers. He pushes hard for the first one and gets back comfortabbly for the second one.
Full length, on leg. Jonny Bairstow clips it to deep square leg for one.
Very full, wide outside off. Jamie Overton reaches out and works it to deep point off the toe-end. He only gets a single.
Good length, wide outside off. Jonny Bairstow punches it to deep point and gets Overton back on strike, who is just 3 short of his ton.
On a length, down the leg side. Jamie Overton tries to tickle it fine but does not connect.
Two dots to end the over! Full length, on off. Jamie Overton defends it out with full face of the blade. He needs to wait for his ton here.
Well he does not have to wait for long. Jonny Bairstow punches this length delivery through point for a single. Jamie Overton gets where he does not want to be - ON STRIKE!
Length ball, on fourth stump. Jamie Overton thinks about flirting with it but defends inside the line.

OUT! CAUGHT! A daggger through the heart. Jamie Overton walks back on 97, a bit disappointed but the crowd is right behind him, as he soaks the applause on his way out. Jonny Bairstow runs across and shares a hug. Could not quiet achieve his personal milestone but he did get his team back into the mix. It is full, outside off. Jamie Overton looks to drive it away but gets the outside edge. The ball goes to first slip and Daryl Mitchell takes a really good low catch. Can New Zealand make the most of the momentum?
Howout: c Daryl Mitchell b Trent Boult

Commentary: Length, on off, defended out.
Outside off, left alone by Broad.
Full length, just outside off. Broad goes after it but misses.
FOUR! Incredible shot! 300 up for England! This is full and wide outside off. Jonny Bairstow slashes it through covers and finds the boundary.
Length ball, around off, nips in a touch. Jonny Bairstow blocks it to cover but gets across for a single anyway.
This one is sprayed down the leg side. Broad is unable to tickle it fine.
Touch fuller, on off, Stuart Broad defends it out solidly.
Full again, on off. Broad defends it back.
BEATEN! On a length, outside off, shaping away a touch. Stuart Broad throws his blade at it but misses. England trail by 28 runs now.
Touch full, on off. Jonny Bairstow uses his feet and pushes it gently towards mid off. He jogs across for a single.
FOUR! This is what Broad was waiting for. He gets off the mark with a fine boundary. Length ball, wide outside off. Stuart Broad stays inside his crease and flays it over covers for a boundary.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Broad. He is not going to stop now. Full length, on fourth stump. Stuart Broad reads it quickly and smacks it over mid off for a boundary.

SIX! BANG! Stuart Broad wants to finish the trail quickly. This one is full and in the slot. Broad moves to the leg side and smokes it over the bowler's head for a biggie. 14 runs off the last three balls.
A dot now! Some breathing space for the bowler. This one is short, outside off. Stuart Broad looks to pull it away but misses.
A single to end the over! Slower full toss, on off. Broad hits it through covers for a single. The trail is just 12 runs now.
FOUR! Stuart Broad is on the charge here! Neil Wagner bowls this full on off stump Stuart Broad makes room and thumps it over long off for a boundary!
Full toss at the waist, bowled slower by Neil Wagner, defended down the pitch by Stuart Broad. Close to being called a no ball.

SIX! Stuart Broad is not just hanging around here! He is erasing the lead in no time! Shorter one this time and on middle, Stuart Broad pulls it over deep square leg for a maximum. 2 more runs to level the score.
Yorker attempted by Neil Wagner, but is full at the pads. Stuart Broad gets his bat down in time and digs the ball out.
Slower delivery once again, short and angled into Stuart Broad. He pulls unconvincingly to deep square leg for a single.
Good-length delivery outside off, Jonny Bairstow knocks it in the cover-point region to get the scores level!
Slightly shorter one down the middle, Jonny Bairstow pulls it towards mid-wicket for one. England now lead by one run.
Shorter and on middle, Stuart Broad looks to pull it but misses.
Back of a length from Trent Boult, Stuart Broad looks to play at it but misses.
Touch fuller and down the middle, Stuart Broad works it straight towards the fielder at short mid-wicket.
Fuller one again and on off, Stuart Broad drives it towards cover for one.
Bowls it on a full length, Jonny Bairstow steers it to covers and straight to the fielder and that will be drinks.
What a beauty to start off from Tim Southee! On a good length pitching on middle, shapes away from Stuart Broad as it beats him all ends up.
Stuart Broad gets down the pitch to a good length delivery on off. Takes a swipe at it and gets beaten once again.
Make that three! Tim Southee bowling a good length and in line with the stumps. Stuart Broad hangs his bat out and gets beaten.
On a good length once again on middle, Stuart Broad connects this time towards cover and gets a single.
Slightly fuller outside off, Jonny Bairstow plays at it and misses.
On middle this time off a good length, Jonny Bairstow works it towards mid-wicket. The diving fielder saves a single.
Michael Bracewell fires this full outside off. Stuart Broad puts his pads to it and New Zealand players appeal. Umpire remains unmoved and they do not review.

FOUR! A lucky boundary from Stuart Broad! Gives the bowler the charge, it's a full delivery outside off. Gets a thick outside edge between keeper and slip to run away to the third man boundary for a four!
Full on middle, Stuart Broad sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.

DROPPED! Full outside off, Jonny Bairstow on the charge thumps it back towards the bowler who gets a hand to it above his head. He can not hang on to the ball as it lobs over him for Jonny Bairstow to get a single.
Length delivery angled into the stumps. Stuart Broad works it leg side.
Full delivery on off, Stuart Broad initially shapes up to sweep but is too full, knocks it towards square leg for a single.
Around the wicket, full and angling in. Stuart Broad fends it towards point.
FOUR! Touch fuller delivery on outside off, Stuart Broad smashes it over covers and towards the extra cover fence for a one-bounce boundary.
FOUR LEG BYES! This one lands outside leg and fuller in length, Stuart Broad looks to flick it but the ball brushes his pads and rolls towards the fine leg fence for another boundary.
Bowls it on a length and on leg, Stuart Broad looks to work it towards mid-wicket but misses as the ball hits his pads and rolls back towards the bowler.
FOUR! That is a good shot! Tim Southee bowls on a good length outside off. Stuart Broad makes room and lifts it over cover to get into his forties!

OUT! BOWLED! Tim Southee does not even celebrate this wicket! Slightly full on middle, shaping away from Stuart Broad who plays the wrong line. The ball shatters against the stumps and Tim Southee jogs towards Stuart Broad giving him the stare! The brisk partnership has come to an end and New Zealand will be hoping to take the remaining two wickets in a hurry!
Howout: b Tim Southee

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT! Jonny Bairstow walks out to a standing ovation. Trent Boult takes a very good catch out on the boundary to end one of the finest innings in Test match cricket. Tossed up on off, Jonny Bairstow looks to hit straight down the ground but miscues it towards long off where Boult takes a diving catch in two hands.
Howout: c Trent Boult b Michael Bracewell

Commentary: FOUR! Off the mark with a boundary! Good-length delivery angling in from off stump. Jack Leach steps back and cuts this past slip towards the third man boundary for a four!

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Jack Leach! Michael Bracewell goes slightly full on off and Jack Leach gives him the charge. Does not time it perfectly but still mangaes to clear the diving mid off player as it runs away for another boundary. These are useful runs for England!
Length ball outside off, Jack Leach steps back and shows his defensive ability.
Full on middle. Jack Leach goes back on the crease and knocks it back towards the bowler.
Good-length delivery outside off stump. Jack Leach leaves this one alone.
Bowls it fuller and outside off, Matthew Potts drives it but finds the fielder at short cover.
Shorter and on off, Potts leaves it through and towards the keeper.
Lands it on a length and down the middle, Potts defends it back towards Tim Southee.
This was close! Bowls it on leg, Potts guides it to covers and takes a single. Kane Williamson has a shy at the bowler's end but misses.
Goes outside off this time, Jack Leach guides it towards the off side.

OUT! LBW! Bowls it on a length and down the middle, Jack Leach looks to play at it but misses as the ball hits his pads. A loud appeal and the finger goes up. Jack Leach goes for a review. Ball Tracking shows three reds and Jack Leach has to walk away. That will be the end of the innings for England and they now lead by 31 runs.
Howout: lbw b Tim Southee

Commentary: Broad starts with a length delivery angling it into the batter, Tom Latham leaves it alone towards the keeper.
Goes on off this time, Tom Latham defends it solidly off the front foot.
Lands it touch fuller in length and down the middle, Latham guides it towards the mid on fielder.
On off and much fuller, Tom Latham pushes it towards covers for three.
Bowls it on middle this time, Will Young defends it solidly.
This one is on a length and outside off, Will Young lets it go.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Tom Latham gets across and flicks it towards the leg side for one.
This is quite fuller and on middle with a hint of turn, Will Young defends it away.
This was similar to the last delivery, Will Young defends it again off his front foot.
On off and fuller in length, Will Young steers it towards point and straight towards the fielder.
Outside off this time, Will Young punches it to covers.
Tossed up on the stumps, Young defends it by getting a stride forward.
Back-of-a-length delivery, way outside off stump. Hits a crack on the surface probably and it seams massively away from the batter. Tom Latham leaves it alone.
Closer to the stumps on a good length, swinging away this time as well. Tom Latham knocks it towards point.
On a good length once again outside off, This one keeps its line as Tom Latham tries to play for the swing. Beats the inside edge of his bat as it flies through to the keeper.
Goes outside off shaping it away, Tom Latham leaves it alone.
Slightly shorter and on middle, Tom Latham eases it towards short covers and scampers for a quick single.
Good-length delivery outside off, left alone by Young.
Flighted up on off, Tom Latham eases it towards short leg.
This one lands fuller and on middle, Tom Latham defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on middle again, Tom Latham leans forward and defends it back towards Jack Leach.
This is similar to the last delivery, Latham again defends it towards the bowler.
Leach bowls it on off, Latham steers it to covers and takes one.
On a length and on off, Will Young leans forward and defends it solidly.
Stuart Broad continues around the wicket to the left-hander. Full and angling into the pads, Tom Latham defends it back to the bowler.
Slightly back of a length outside off. Tom Latham plays at it and gets a thickish edge along the ground towards gully.
Good-length delivery outside off, Tom Latham leaves it alone!
FOUR! Lovely drive from Tom Latham! Stuart Broad goes full outside off, Tom Latham gets a stride forward and times it beautifully through the vacant mid-off area for a boundary!
Stuart Broad goes full, on middle and shapes it away from the batter. Tom Latham tries to work this leg side but gets a leading edge that skims through backward point and they run two.
Full again this time angling into the pads, Tom Latham flicks it down to fine leg for a single. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 3.

WOAH! This one was close. Potts starts with a wobble seam. This one is on a length, outside off, nips back in sharply. Tom Latham decides to leave it but never thought of the inward movement. It comes off his gloves and bounces in front of the stumps.
Length, on the pads, Latham tucks it to the leg side.
On a length, around off, Latham remains solid in his defense.
Full length, around the pads, Latham tucks it to mid-wicket and gets across for a quick single.
This one shapes in, full and on off. Will Young stays back and defends it back watchfully.
Good length, outside off, shapes in a touch. Young leaves it alone.
Touch fuller, on off, angled in on off. Latham defends it out solidly on the front foot.
Tom Latham continues to score in this innings! He moves to 13. This one is on a length, outside off. Tom Latham punches it through covers for three runs.
Length ball, on top of off. Young defends it to the leg side.
Good length, outside off. Young lets it go to the keeper.
BEATEN! This one is on a length, around off, shaping away. Young looks to drive it away but gets beaten on the outside edge. He is yet to get off the mark.
FOUR! Young is off the mark. Full length, outside off. Young goes for the drive as he leans in, it goes off the outer half, past backward point for a boundary.
Length and on off. Latham punches it through covers on his back foot and gets a brace.
Back of a length, outside off. Latham cuts it hard towards backward point but could only get a single.
FOUR! Young gets lucky this time! Potts angles it in and makes it shape away. Young defends with soft hands. It goes through the slip cordon off the outside edge. He is yet to find his feet.
Length, on off, defended out.
Touch shorter, on off. Ypung taps it to point.

OUT! CAUGHT! Matthew Potts draws the first blood. Will Young could not find his feet and perishes at a timid score. He is not happy with himself. This is full, outside off. Will Young tries to drive it away with hard-hands this time. He is unable to time it well and finds the outside edge. Ollie Pope takes a sharp catch at gully.
Howout: c Ollie Pope b Matthew Potts

Commentary: FOUR! Tom Latham continues on his merry way. It is full, on the pads, Latham comes inside the line and tucks it through square leg for four.
Length and on off. Latham pushes it to mid off.
Full length, on the pads, Latham tucks it to mid on. Jack Leach makes a brilliant stop and allows just a single.
LEG BYE! Back of a length, around the pads, Williamson fails to flick it away. It goes to square leg off the pads. They collect a leg bye.
On a length, just outside off. Latham dabs it to gully but denies for a single.
A single to end the over! Full length, goind down leg. Latham stays back and clips it to square leg for a single. A tidy over by Broad comes to an end.
Matthew Potts has his hands over his head! This one shapes in from outside off, on a length. Tom Latham gets an inside edge onto his pads. He does enough to avert the danger.
Good length, shapes in a touch. Latham blocks it out watchfully.
Full length, on off. Latham gets across and tucks it to the leg side.
Much quicker this time. Good length, on the fourth stump. Latham covers his stumps and shoulders his arms at it.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! This is full and on off. Tom Latham drives it down the ground towards long on for four.
Length ball, on off. Latham comes behind the line and blocks it out.
Full length, on off. Kane Williamson smothers it to point and is quick to get across for a single.
Tom Latham shuffles across and tucks this length delivery to the leg side.
Much straighter this time. On a length, outside off. Latham leaves it alone.
Three dots in a row! Full length, angled in on off. Latham defends it solidly.
Length ball, outside off. Latham remains solid in his defense.
Broad fires in a yorker, right in the blockhole. Latham is up to the challenge and digs it out with ease. Five dots on the trot to end the over.
Full length, outside off. Williamson blocks it to point.
This is angled in on off. Williamson defends it out on his back foot and denies for the single.
Fraction short, around off. Kane Williamson is on his toes to block out.
Much fuller, on off. Kane Williamson defends it out to covers. No runs off the over so far.
Length, on off, blocked back to the bowler.
A single to end the over then. Full length, on the pads, Kane Williamson clips it through square leg for a single. They lead by 10 runs.
Length ball, on the pads, Williamson tucks it fine but finds the fielder there.
Back of a length, on off. Kane Williamson blocks it to mid on.
Good length, on fifth stump. Williamson gets across and defends it into the deck. He could've easily left this ball.
A sharp bouncer this time, on off. Kane Williamson ducks under it wisely.
Jamie Overton sprays this one down leg, very full. Williamson tries to tuck it away but misses. Ben Stokes dives to his left and gathers the ball.
A maiden for Overton to start with. Touch short, outside off. Williamson defends it out watchfully.

BYE! How has this missed the stumps! Incredible bowling by Potts. This one nips in sharply from outside off. Latham gets beaten on the inside edge. There is some sound but the umpire signals byes, as the batters cross for a single. Jonny Bairstow was also undone by the movement here.
Length ball, around off. Kane Williamson defends it out watchfully.
Shorter, outside off, Williamson punches it to covers.
Full length, outside off, gets it to shape in late. Kane Williamson lets it through.
Angled into the pads, Kane Williamson defends it out solidly.
This is outside off, Kane Williamson leaves it alone.
Tom Latham is angry with himself. Good length, around off, shaping away from the left-hander. It spits off the deck. Latham tries to cut it away but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length ball, on off. Latham pushes it to covers for a single.
FOUR! Easy pickings for Kane Williamson. It is full, on the pads. Williamson flicks it through square leg for a fine boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
Length ball, around the hips. Kane Williamson tucks it to mid-wicket and gets across for a single.
FOUR! Second boundary of the over. A great over for New Zealand. This is full and outside off. Tom Latham leans in and creams it through covers for a boundary.
Flighted full on leg stump, defended towards mid on.
Good-length delivery on off, Kane Williamson goes back and cuts it towards point.
Full on leg once again, knocked towards the leg side.
Straighter delivery on a good length. Kane Williamson defends this back to the bowler.
Pulls back the length a bit on middle, Kane Williamson rocks back and defends it down the pitch.
Tossed up full on middle, Kane Williamson takes a big stride forward and smothers the ball.
Bowls a shorter one at 84 MPH, Latham ducks underneath it.
FOUR! This one lands fuller and outside off, Latham looks to drive it but gets a thick outside edge. The ball races towards the third man and behind the fence for a boundary.
Shorter delivery on middle. Tom Latham nudges it leg side.
Back of a length once again outside off. Tom Latham places it wide off cover for a single.
Short and angled into the batter, Kane Williamson ducks under this one.
Full and angled in from off stump. Steady defense from Kane Williamson back to the bowler.
Full delivery outside off, Tom Latham gets forward and knocks it towards mid-wicket.
Middle stump line bowled on a good length, Tom Latham works this towards square leg for a single.
Flighted this one full on off, Kane Williamson opens the face of the bat and places it past the cover fielder for a brace.
Flighted once again, full on middle. Kane Williamson defends this back down the pitch.
Full on middle, slightly quicker, Kane Williamson defends towards short leg.
Full and angling onto the pads. Kane Williamson knocks it down towards short leg once again.
Jamie Overton goes around the wicket and bangs it short angling into the batter. Tom Latham fends it with one hand down towards the leg side.
Fuller this time, angling in from off. Defended back towards the bowler.
Goes fuller, on middle. Tom Latham solid in defence as he knocks it back to Jamie Overton.
Back-of-a-length delivery trying to cramp the batter. Tom Latham works it with soft hands towards square leg for a single.
Goes really short outside off, Kane Williamson thinks about playing the upper cut and decides against it at the last moment.
Good-length delivery on off stump. Kane Williamson is in complete control of his defense.
Full and angling in from off, Tom Latham works it across his pads towards leg slip.
Fullish on the middle and leg, it is again defended towards short leg.
Flatter from outside off, Tom Latham tries to sweep and misses, hits his body.
Full on off stump. defended towards mid on.
Full once again on the same line, Tom Latham defends it back to the bowler.
Tom Latham charges the bowler and catches the ball on the full outside off. Hits it back to the bowler who collects it and takes a shy at the striker's end.
Length delivery, on the off stump, Williamson covers the line and defends it.
Overton bowls it outside off this time, Kane Williamson leaves it alone.
On off, Kane Williamson defends it solidly.
Overton serves it on a length and outside off, Kane Williamson guides it towards the fielder at point.
This was similar to the last delivery, Kane Williamson again guides it towards the point fielder.
Shorter one on leg, Kane Williamson ducks under it. Wide called.
This one lands on a length and on middle, Kane Williamson defends it off the front foot.
Fuller and on middle, Latham sweeps it towards backward square leg where the fielder makes a diving stop. A couple of runs taken.
Quicker one on middle, Latham works it towards mid-wicket for one.
Tossed up delivery, on the stumps, Williamson prods forward and defends it solidly.
FOUR! Short ball and on off, Kane Williamson uses the pace of the ball and cuts it towards third man for a boundary.
Tossed up delivery, this is played towards covers for one.
Jack Leach bowls it outside off, Latham defends it towards the off side.
FOUR! Fuller and outside off, Kane Williamson drives it past covers for a boundary. This was perfectly timed from Kane Williamson.
Fuller and on middle, this is defended towards the leg side.
FOUR! On a length and on leg, Kane Williamson flicks it towards deep square leg. The fielder chases it but cannot reach it and the ball goes behind the fence for a boundary.
On middle this time, Kane Williamson defends it away. Oh, its a no ball.
Fuller one and down the leg side, Kane Williamson flicks it towards square leg for one.
FOUR! Short and punished! Slightly shorter and on off, Latham punches it past covers for a boundary. He moves to 49.
Fifty up for Tom Latham. On off and touch fuller in length, Latham guides it to covers for one.
Tossed up outside off, Tom Latham leans forward and blocks it away.
On middle this time, Latham uses his feet and guides it towards the leg side.
Tossed up, on the stumps, swept straight to the fielder.
Length ball on middle, Latham eases it towards the leg side again.
FOUR! On middle and fuller, Latham sweeps it towards deep square leg for a boundary. Excellent shot from Tom Latham.
This is outside off and spins back in a long way, Latham goes on the back and keeps the ball away. An appeal but the umpire is not interested.
Outside off, left alone.
This is fuller and on off, Kane Williamson defends it towards the off side.
Fuller one again, Kane Williamson flicks it but finds the fielder at short mid-wicket.
Slightly shorter one and on off, Kane Williamson punches it towards the point fielder.
This one lands fuller and down the middle, Kane Williamson nudges it towards the short mid-wicket fielder.
Fuller and on off, Kane Williamson drives it towards long off. A long chase from the substitute fielder who saves it just before the fence. Three runs taken.
Tossed up on middle, Kane Williamson punches it towards the cover fielder.
Fuller and on middle, this is blocked out solidly.
Flighted up on middle, Kane Williamson eases it towards the short leg fielder.
Tossed up outside off, Kane Williamson drives it towards covers and scampers through for a single. Direct hit on the stumps and the ball rolls towards third man. Two runs taken.
Flighted on off stump. Kane Williamson defends this towards cover.
FOUR! Jack Leach goes short and wide, Kane Williamson gets low and cuts this through point for a boundary! Kane Williamson getting a move on now and is looking good!
Good-length delivery from over the wicket, angling into Tom Latham. He fends it towards point.
FOUR! Great timing from Tom Latham! Ben Stokes goes full on the pads looking for swing. Does not find any and Tom Latham flicks this easily through mid-wicket for a boundary!

FOUR! That is an action replay! Ben Stokes is bwling too full and angling down leg. Tom Latham is timing the ball wonderfully and manages to pierce the gap between mid-wicket and mid on for the second boundary of the over.
Full outside off, worked towards covers.
Ben Stokes finally gets it right. Good-length delivery just outside off, swings away from Tom Latham and beats him all ends up.
Straying down leg side once again, Tom Latham flicks this square this time straight to the fielder at square leg.
On off, defended out.
Fuller and on middle, Kane Williamson defends it back towards Jack Leach.
This one lands outside off, Kane Williamson defends it with soft hands towards the off side.
Tossed up on leg, Kane Williamson guides it towards the fielder at short leg.
Tossed up outside off with a hint of turn, Kane Williamson gets in two minds but leaves it alone in the end.
Good-length delivery on middle. Kane Williamson goes back and knocks it towards short mid-wicket.

FOUR! Ben Stokes has got his length all wrong here! Coming from around the wicket bowls it full on the pads all over again. Tom Latham is happy to work this towards mid-wicket and get himself four more runs.
On a good length this time outside off, Tom Latham leaves this one alone.
Good-length delivery on off, Tom Latham defends this towards mid on.
Fraction fuller outside off, Tom Latham knocks it towards short cover.
Full and angling in from off stump. Tom Latham gets forward and strokes it towards mid off.
Good-length delivery this time outside off. Tom Blundell solid in defense as he plays it towards covers.
Flighted on a good length outside off, Kane Williamson leaves it alone.
Fuller on middle, Kane Williamson works it towards mid-wicket.
Full once again and sticks to the middle stump line, Kane Williamson defends towards point.
Full outside off stump, Kane Williamson goes forward and defends well.
Good-length delivery on leg, plays it towards short leg.
Shorter this time outside off. Kane Williamson goes back and works it towards short third man.
FOUR! Stuart Broad follows suit and continues to feed Tom Latham on his pads! Full and Tom Latham once again places it towards the mid-wicket boundary!
Full and angling onto the pads once again. Tom Latham works this to square leg for a brace.
Full outside off this time. Tom Latham leaves this one alone.

DROPPED! Joe Root has dropped a sitter! Stuart Broad brought back into the attack almost delivered for England, but some ordinary catching has given Tom Latham an extra life! Stuart Broad bowls this full outside off. Tom Latham has been timing it well and decides to go after this one but only manages to get an outside edge towards first slip. Joe Root at first slip goes on one knee to catch this but the ball drops from his hand! What a let off for New Zealand!
Goes outside off this time, Latham leaves it alone.
This was similar to the last delivery, Latham again leaves it through and towards the keeper.
Full and outside off, pushes it past cover for a single.
Goes outside off with a hint of turn, Latham looks to defend it but misses.
FOUR! This one lands outside leg, Latham uses the pace of the ball and flicks it towards fine leg for a boundary.
Fuller and on middle, this is defended off the front foot.
Goes fuller again, Tom Latham defends it away solidly.
Fuller and on off, Latham defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Fraction short and on middle. Kane Williamson rolls his wrist and pulls it wide of deep square leg for a boundary!
Full on off stump. Kane Williamson knocks it back to the bowler who parries it towards mid off.
Stuart Broad bowls this one wide from off stump on a good length. Kane Williamson leaves it alone.
Slightly closer to the stumps this time on a good length. Kane Williamson judges it well and leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery on off. Kane Williamson gets forward and defends firmly.
Goes a little fuller outside off. Kane Williamson watches it carefully and lets it through to the keeper. The umpires have decided that it shall be Tea on DAY 3.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Jamie Overton strikes right after tea! Bowls this on a good length just outside off, gets lovely shape away from Tom Latham who had been playing beautifully before the break. Gets an outside edge straight to Jonny Bairstow who takes an easy catch! What a start for England!
Howout: c Jonny Bairstow b Jamie Overton

Commentary: Jamie Overton is on fire here! What a first ball to Devon Conway as he bangs it in short and the ball thuds against his helmet. Completely floors the batter.
Back-of-a-length delivery aimed for the batter. Devon Conway tries to pull and gets hit on the body this time.
FOUR! An unconvincing shot to get off the mark! Jamie Overton goes a touch fuller outside off, Devon Conway hangs his bat out and get a thick outside edge past the slip cordon for a boundary!
On a good length and down the middle, this is defended off the front foot.
Slightly back of a length outside off, Devon Conway works this through cover-point for a couple of runs.
Loose delivery to start off with for Stuart Broad. Bowls this full and really wide from off stump. Kane Williamson does not bother with it.
Good-length delivery outside off. Fended towards point.
Slightly full on off, Kane Williamson taps it on the offside.
Good delivery from Stuart Broad as he beats Kane Williamson on his outside edge. Just outside off on a good length, moves away from the batter.
Full and outside off, Kane Williamson uses his wrists and works it towards square leg for a single.
Bowls this fraction back of a length outside off. Gets an extra bit of bounce from the surface and Devon Conway gets on top of this and works it down to his feet.
On a length and on middle, Kane Williamson looks to flick it but gets an outside edge as the ball rolls towards the vacant silly point region.
This one lands on a length as well, Kane Williamson defends it back towards Jamie Overton.
Wayward bouncer from Jamie Overton, Kane Williamson leaves it alone towards the keeper.
Slightly shorter and on middle, Kane Williamson flicks it towards square leg for one.
Goes fuller and down the middle, Devon Conway eases it back towards Jamie Overton.
FOUR! Shorter one outside off, Devon Conway waits for the ball and plays a late cut towards third man. The ball goes behind the fence for a boundary.
Fuller one on middle, this one is lower, Kane Williamson blocks it out solidly.
Oh, that was close! On a length and just outside off, Kane Williamson looks to block it but misses. The ball just aired past his bat and into the gloves of the keeper.
FOUR! Fuller and outside off, Kane Williamson looks to defend it but gets a thick outside edge as the ball races towards the third man fence for a boundary.
This one lands fuller and on middle, Kane Williamson defends it away.
Outside off this time, left alone by Kane Williamson.
On a length and on off, Kane Williamson guides it towards the mid off fielder.

Oh, this was close. Shorter and on middle, Devon Conway pulls it towards square leg where Ben Stokes makes a diving effort to catch it but just gets his fingertips at it and goes towards deep square leg. They rotate the strike.
Shorter once again, Kane Williamson leaves it alone. Oh, its a no ball.
This one lands fuller and on middle, Kane Williamson defends it away.
On a length and outside leg, Kane Williamson leaves it alone.
On a length and outside leg, Kane Williamson looks to flick it but misses. A loud shout but the finger stays down.
Shorter one this time, Kane Williamson leaves it alone towards the keeper.
FOUR! This one lands fuller and outside leg, Kane Williamson just gives a fine tickle to it as the ball races towards the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Outside off this time, Devon Conway drives it towards the short cover fielder who does a funny impression and throws the ball in the air.
Stuart Broad bowls it outside off, Devon Conway shoulders arms at it.
Fuller one on leg, Devon Conway works it towards the mid-wicket fielder.
This one lands outside off, Devon Conway lets it through and towards the keeper.
Slightly shorter and just outside off, Devon Conway shoulders arms to it.
Outside off again from Stuart Broad, left alone by Devon Conway.
Shorter one outside off shaping it away, Kane Williamson leaves it alone towards the keeper.
Jamie Overton serves a length ball on off, Kane Williamson blocks it towards the mid off fielder.
Shorter and outside off, Kane Williamson leaves it alone.
Shorter one again and outside off, Kane Williamson lets it through and towards the keeper.
Shorter one again, much slower this time, Kane Williamson lets this one go as well.
On a length and much fuller, Kane Williamson defends it off the front foot.
Flights one full outside off to start off with. Devon Conway gets a long way across and defends it.
On a length outside off, Conway leans forward and defends it.
Full once again outside off, defended towards point.
On a good length outside off, Devon Conway goes on the backfoot and defends.
Angled in from off stump, Devon Conway plays with soft hands towards cover.
Full and wide outside off. Devon Conway strides across once again and defends solidly.
Starts with a tossed-up delivery outside off, Williamson defends it with a big stride forward.
Short and wide, a little bit of an extra bounce. Kane Williamson works it to backward point for a single.

Full and going down leg stump, Devon Conway tries to work it fine but misses. So does Jonny Bairstow as he can not get down in time. Runs down to the fine leg boundary for four byes. The rain has gotten heavy and umpires ask the players to leave the field.

OUT! CAUGHT! The break has worked once again! England strike on a restart once again! What a catch from Ollie Pope as he plucks it out of thin air. Good-length delivery on the middle, Conway tries to defend gets a thick inside edge towards short leg! New Zealand are three down now!
Howout: c Ollie Pope b Joe Root

Commentary: This is outside off with a hint of turn, left alone by Henry Nicholls.
Fuller and on middle, this is flicked towards the leg side for one.
Stuart Broad bowls a good length delivery on off from round the wicket, Nicholls defends it solidly in the off side.
Back of a length outside off, Henry Nicholls covers the line of the ball and defends it solidly.
Fraction full outside off, Henry Nicholls leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery wide from off stump. Henry Nicholls shoulders arms to it.
Slightly full and angled towards the leg side. Henry Nicholls tries to work it leg side but gets a leading edge towards cover.
Wide delivery once again on a good length. Henry Nicholls happy to let this one go as well.
Slightly back of a length on off, Kane Williamson rises up and fends it on the offside.
Good-length delivery angled into the pads. Gets to Kane Williamson quicker then he expects and gets a leading edge to short cover.
Full on middle, keeps a fraction low. Kane Williamson gets his bat down in time and plays it back to the bowler.
Wide outside off, Kane Williamson not tempted to play at that one.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Matthew Potts gets Kane Williamson fishing once again! Good-length delivery from outside off, Matthew Potts gets the ball to hold the line. Kane Williamson plays before the angle and gets a edge to Jonny Bairstow who has no trouble pouching this one! The skipper departs and New Zealand are falling apart after the rain interval! Matthew Potts has got Kane Williamson 3 out of 4 times in this series now.
Howout: c Jonny Bairstow b Matthew Potts

Commentary: On a length and on leg, Daryl Mitchell defends it towards the leg side.
On a length and on middle, Henry Nicholls with a solid block off his front foot.
Fuller one this time on off, Henry Nicholls works it towards short mid-wicket fielder.
Not short enough to cut, and Henry Nicholls slashes at it and misses.
Full angled into the stumps, Henry Nicholls knocks it towards cover. Headingly is buzzing! They are pumped up and all the English players are joining in on the fun!
Full outside off, Daryl Mitchell steps across and defends it confidently.
Good-length delivery outside off, Daryl Mitchell watches it closely and leaves it alone.
Full delivery holding its line outside off, Henry Nicholls leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Full once again but closer to the batter. Henry Nicholls knocks it towards cover.
Good-length delivery outside off, Henry Nicholls steps across and plays it firmly towards cover.
Full this time angling into the pads, Henry Nicholls defends and gets an inside edge towards sqaure leg for a single.
Full delivery angling in from outside off. Daryl Mitchell shuffles across and taps it towards the leg side.
Good outswinger outside off, Daryl Mitchell leaves this one well.
Good-length delivery outside off. Defended back to the bowler.
FOUR! That is beautifully timed by Henry Nicholls! Full on the pads, Henry Nicholls flicks it through the midwicket region for a boundary! England has conceded a lot of runs in that region!
Good-length delivery on off, Henry Nicholls gets across and defends solidly.
Slightly full outside off, Henry Nicholls gets low and lets the ball pass through to the keeper.
Off stump line on a good length. Henry Nicholls defends it towards point.
What a delivery to the end the over! On a good length just outside off, bowls from wide off the crease and makes the ball hold its line. Henry Nicholls is beaten all ends up.
Goes fuller and down the leg side, Daryl Mitchell defends it towards the fielder at mid on.
On a length and outside off, Daryl Mitchell guides it towards short cover.
Oh, that was close. On a length and on off, Daryl Mitchell looks to defend it but misses as the ball goes just past his blade and towards the keeper.
This is fuller and on middle, this is defended back towards the bowler.
Flicks a length ball towards the mid on fielder.
Daryl Mitchell is off the mark. Fuller and on leg, Daryl Mitchell flicks it towards backward square leg for one.
On a full length and on middle, this is flicked towards the leg side for one.
Fuller one on middle, blocked away.
Tossed up on middle, Henry Nicholls defends it back towards the bowler.
This is similar to the last delivery, this is again defended towards the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT! Fuller one again with a hint of turn, Henry Nicholls comes forward to defend it but the ball hits the upper part of his bat and carries towards Jack Leach who takes a diving catch with his both hands. New Zealand has lost 5 wickets for just 161 now!
Howout: c & b Jack Leach

Commentary: This one lands on the leg side, Tom Blundell defends it towards the leg side.
Good-length delivery on off. Daryl Mitchell punches it back and Matthew Potts catches the ball on his follow-through.
Length delivery outside off, defended back to the bowler.
Goes short angling into Daryl Mitchell who mistimes his pull towards mid-wicket for a single.
Fraction full on middle, Tom Blundell works it towards square leg.
Good-length delivery bowled in line with the stump. Tom Blundell knocks it back to the bowler.
Yorker length on off stump, Tom Blundell manages to dig this one out.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell nudges it towards the mid-wicket region for one.
On middle this time, Tom Blundell blocks it off his front foot.
Sticks to bowling it on middle, this is again defended back towards Jack Leach.
On middle again, Tom Blundell looks to defend it but gets an inside edge as the ball rolls towards the leg gully.
Fuller and on middle, Tom Blundell flicks it towards the leg side for one.
This one lands fuller and on middle, Daryl Mitchell watchfully blocks it away.
On a length and on middle, Tom Blundell defends it towards the mid on fielder.
On middle and fuller in length, this is guided towards the mid on fielder.
FOUR! Fuller one on middle and leg, Tom Blundell uses the pace of the ball and flicks it towards fine leg for a boundary.
A yorker on leg, Tom Blundell looks to defend it but misses as the ball hits his toe. A loud shout but the finger stays down.
This one lands on leg as well, Tom Blundell defends it solidly.
FOUR! Potts starts with a length delivery on the pads, Blundell tucks it nicely through square leg and it races away to the fence. A perfect start for New Zealand.
Stuart Broad starts with a full outside off. Daryl Mitchell defends back to the bowler.
Fuller this time and wider from off stump, Daryl Mitchell strides forward and hits it straight to short cover.
Good-length delivery outside off, Daryl Mitchell happy to leave this one alone.
Nice shape away from Daryl Mitchell. Stuart Broad bowls this on a good length outside off. Daryl Mitchell steps across towards the offside and hangs his bat out but gets beaten.
Fraction shorter but still outside off. Daryl Mitchell shoulders arms to it.
Fuller and outside off, Daryl Mitchell leaves this one for the keeper to collect.
Matthew Potts delivers this slightly full and outside off stump. Tom Blundell not interested to play at it.
Good-length delivery, angling in from outside off, Tom Blundell judges the line of the ball well and leaves it.
Middle stump line on a good length, Tom Blundell knocks it down on the leg side.
FOUR! Tom Blundell gets the second boundary of the morning! Full and on off, Tom Blundell strides forward and guides it past short cover for a boundary!
Fuller on off stump, blocked towards covers.
Good-length delivery outside off, Left alone by Tom Blundell.
This one lands shorter and outside off, Daryl Mitchell lets it go towards the keeper.
Stuart Broad bowls it on off this time, Daryl Mitchell defends it back to him.
Goes fuller and on leg, Daryl Mitchell eases it straight towards the mid on fielder.
Slightly full and angling in from outside off. Daryl Mitchell raises his hands and lets it through.
Full once again on off, Sturdy defense back to the bowler from Daryl Mitchell.
Pulls his length back a bit on middle. Daryl Mitchell works it towards short mid-wicket. 2 maidens for Stuart Broad to begin proceedings!
Good length, wide outside off. Tom Blundell shoulders his arms at it.
Touch short, around the hips. Tom Blundell tucks it to the leg side.
Length ball, on off. Blundell flicks it towards mid-wicket.
BEATEN! Matthew Potts bowling with fire here. On a length, wide outside off. Blundell presses forward and tries to work it away but misses. He gets beaten on his outside edge.
Incredible bowling! This one angles in but straightens off the deck. Tom Blundell yet again defends inside the line and misses the ball completely.
A maiden for Matthew Potts. Full length, on off. Tom Blundell blocks it out.
Length, around off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it to the on side.
Full length this time, angled into the pads, Daryl Mitchell stays back and drives it towards mid on with soft-hands.
Fraction short, way outside off. Daryl Mitchell shoulders his arms at it.
Touch short, on off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it out.
Fuller in length, much straighter on off. Daryl Mitchell defends it back.
Good shot but straight to the fielder. Full length, outside off. Daryl Mitchell connects sweetly and drives it to short extra cover. Could not find the gap.
Good length, outside off, with a bit of movement. Tom Blundell leaves it alone.
On a length, on fifth stump. Tom Blundell presses forward and blocks it to the off side.
This is touch shorter, wide outside off. Tom Blundell does not chase it at all.
Wide outside off yet again. Tom Blundell strides across and shoulders his arms at it.
This is much fuller, outside off, shaping away a touch. Tom Blundell lets it go through.

Great delivery to end the over! This time it is close to the batter but still did not force Blundell to play at it. It is on a length, in the corridor of uncertainty. Tom Blundell squares up a bit, as he shuffles across and tries to block it out. He keeps the blade close to the body, as the ball zips past the outside edge.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Full length, on middle and leg. Daryl Mitchell stays back and clips it through square leg for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.

RIPPER! This one lands outside off and nips back in sharply. Daryl Mitchell is caught inside his crease and gets beaten on the inside edge. This is as close as it gets. Broad asking the right questions here.
Fuller, on off. Mitchell blocks it to the on side.
Brilliant running this time! It is full, on middle and leg. Daryl Mitchell clips it to deep square leg and gets back for the second run.
Length, on the pads, Daryl Mitchell flicks it to square leg for one. A good over for the visitors, 7 runs off it.
Potts angles it from outside off, but this one straightens after hitting the deck. Daryl Mitchell shows no interest to play away from his body.
Two dots in a row now! It is angled into the pads, on a length. Daryl Mitchell stays back, closes the face of the blade and blocks it towards mid on.
On a length, outside off. Daryl Mitchell defends it to point on the front foot. Three dots now. Potts has been clinical so far this morning.
Make it 4 now! Length ball, on off. Daryl Mitchell remains solid in his defense.
Full-length delivery, on fifth stump. Daryl Mitchell leans in and drives it to covers. The fielder dives to his left to make a great stop.
On leg, Daryl Mitchell works it to the leg side. Potts records his fifth maiden of this innings.
Broad serves it full, outside off. Tom Blundell strides across and shoulders his arms at it.
Really good running! This is full and on off. Tom Blundell is forced to play at it this time. He digs it out to backward point and scampers across for a single.
Fraction short, on off. Daryl Mitchell is on his toes to defend it out.
Length, on off. Mitchell blocks it out.
A sharp bouncer this time, on middle and leg. Daryl Mitchell ducks under it without any second thoughts.
Four dots on the trot to end the over! Stuart Broad goes with the bouncer yet again, around off. Daryl Mitchell bends his knees and leaves it alone.
Tossed up on middle, this is blocked back towards the bowler.
Looped up, around off, defended out.
Floated and full, around off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it on his front foot.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Mitchell presses forward and blocks it to the on side.
Back of a length, outside off. Mitchell goes back and dabs it towards point.
Just a single of the over! It is full and on off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it back to the bowler.
FOUR! A loosener to start with. Full length, angling down leg. Tom Blundell stays back and flicks it through square leg for a boundary.
Full length, around off. Blundell eases it towards mid on.
Length ball, outside off, shapes in a touch. Tom Blundell stays back and defends it out watchfully.
This very full just outside off. Tom Blundell digs it out to backward point.
Good comeback by Overton. Short ball, on top of off. Blundell stays inside the crease and digs it out.
5 dots in a row to end the over. This is on a length, around off. Tom Blundell defends it out.
Looped up, around off. Daryl Mitchell defends it to the leg side.
FOUR! Swept away nicely. It is full and outside off. Daryl Mitchell gets down on one knee and sweeps it from outside off towards deep square leg for a boundary.
On off, defended back to the bowler on the front foot.
Floated and full, around leg. Daryl Mitchell goes for the sweep again but this time is unable to clear Jamie Overton at short fine leg.
On middle and leg, tucked to the on side.
Tossed up, full and on off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it watchfully. New Zealand lead by 162 runs now.
FOUR! Nicely played! It is short, around middle. Tom Blundell stays back and pulls it through square leg. He does enough to keep the ball grounded and sees it racing towards the boundary.
Back of a length, outside off. Tom Blundell defends it on his toes.
A single now! Short ball, on off. Tom Blundell taps it down to point and scampers through as there is no fielder placed close by.
Length ball, on off. Daryl Mitchell works it towards mid on but denies against the single in the end.
Back of a length, on off. Daryl Mitchell rides the bounce and pulls it towards square but straight to the fielder.
Full length, on the pads. Daryl Mitchell nudges it to mid-wicket and steals a single. He will retain the strike.
Tossed up on middle, this is blocked back towards the bowler.
On off this time, Daryl Mitchell eases it towards the off side.

FOUR LEG BYES! That's a jaffa. On middle with some turn, Daryl Mitchell looks to defend it but misses. The keeper misses it s well as the ball races towards the long stop and behind the fence. Unlucky for Jack Leach.
Flighted delivery down the middle, Daryl Mitchell defends it on the front foot.
Tossed up on off, Daryl Mitchell punches it straight towards the cover fielder.
Full on the pads, Daryl Mitchell fends it towards short mid on.
This one lands shorter and outside off, Tom Blundell looks to pull it but misses.
Shorter one again, Tom Blundell pulls it this time but finds the fielder at deep square leg. Single taken.
On leg and fuller in length, Daryl Mitchell flicks it towards mid-wicket for one.
Jamie Overton bowls a bouncer down the middle, Tom Blundell looks to play at it but misses.
Back of a length this time, Tom Blundell lets it go.
Another bouncer down the leg side, Tom Blundell leaves it alone. Wide called.
Change of line. Jamie Overton bowls it outside off this time, Tom Blundell blocks it away.
This one lands fuller and outside off, Daryl Mitchell guides it to the mid off fielder.
Outside off this time with some turn, Daryl Mitchell looks to block it but misses.
This one lands on middle, Daryl Mitchell eases it back towards the bowler.
Fuller one and on leg, Daryl Mitchell sweeps it but finds the fielder at square leg.
On middle this time, Daryl Mitchell blocks it away.

NOT OUT! Daryl Mitchell extends his stay in the middle with the help of DRS. It is tossed up, around off. Daryl Mitchell gets on his front foot, tries to block it out but gets beaten and gets pinged on his pads. Leach appeals and the finger goes up. The review is taken. UltraEdge shows no bat is involved. The Ball Tracking shows that the ball is missing the wickets. Jack Leach is disappointed after looking at the big screen.
Shorter and on middle, Tom Blundell pulls it towards backward square leg for one.
On a length and outside off, Daryl Mitchell guides it towards covers for a quick single.
FOUR! Shorter and on middle, Tom Blundell pulls it hard and towards deep square leg for a boundary.  This brings up 50 runs partnership between Tom Blundell and Daryl Mitchell.
On middle and on a length, this is pulled towards mid-wicket for one.
This one lands outside off, Mitchell leaves it alone.
Goes 'round the wicket and bowls a shorter one outside off, Daryl Mitchell ducks under it.
Tossed up on middle with some turn, Tom Blundell goes on his back foot and guides it towards the leg side.
