On off this time, Tom Blundell blocks it away.
This is much fuller in length, Tom Blundell defends it back towards the bowler.
Flighted delivery on middle, Blundell strides forward as he defends it solidly.
This is on middle and fuller, Blundell flicks it towards the leg side and towards the fielder.
On a length this time, Blundell makes some room for himself as he cuts it towards point for a single.
Around the wicket on a good length, angling away from Tom Blundell. He taps it down towards cover with soft hands and gets a single.
Shorter this time on leg, Daryl Mitchell ducks under this one.

Good-length delivery pitching outside leg, Daryl Mitchell tries to pull but is not short enough and hits him high on his pads. The ball loops up and Jamie Overton catches it. Initially appeals for LBW and then for a catch, the umpire gives it not out.
Dug in short down leg side, Daryl Mitchell lets this pass through to the keeper.
WIDE! Really short and Daryl Mitchell does not even need to duck for this one. Given wide for height.
Slightly shorter one on off, this is punched towards covers for one.
FOUR! That goes fine for a boundary! The short deliveries not working as Jamie Overton strays down leg and Tom Blundell gets a bit of bat on it. Runs away to the fine leg boundary for four runs!
Full outside off, Daryl Mitchell brings his front foot outside the line of the stumps and sweeps it to backward square leg for a single.
Fraction short on off, Tom Blundell goes on his back foot and gets a single to point.
Full and on off, Daryl Mitchell works it towards cover-point for a single.
Full and angled into the pads, Tom Blundell drops it down towards short leg.
Full once again on middle, Tom Blundell gets forward in defense and it falls towards short-leg.
Outside off stump and full. Tom Blundell is solid in defense.
FOUR! Joe Root begins his spell by being reverse swept! Bowls this full outside off, Daryl Mitchell gets on his knees and connects well enough to find the third man boundary!

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries! He tries to reverse sweep it but was slightly early in the shot. It hit the glove and initially was going in the direction of Crawley who was moving to his right at first slip. However, it ended up going past the left of Crawley as it hit the toe-end of the bat in the follow through and goes to the fine leg fence.
Fuller and down the leg side, Daryl Mitchell flicks it towards backward square leg for a brace.
Touch fuler and outside off, this is defended towards the mid off fielder.
On middle and tossed up, Daryl Mitchell guides it back towards the bowler.
This one lands fuller and on middle with some turn, Daryl Mitchell eases it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on middle, this is defended off the front foot.
Jack Leach bowls it on middle, Tom Blundell guides it towards the off side.
On a length and on leg, Tom Blundell flicks it towards square leg for one.
Flighted on off, Daryl Mitchell solid once again.
Full and angled into the stumps, knocked towards the bowler.
Length delivery outside off, worked to deep cover-point for a single.
Flighted up delivery outside off, Daryl Mitchell defends it towards the off side.
FOUR! Fuller and on off, Daryl Mitchell uses his feet and lofts it towards long on for a one-bounce boundary.
FOUR! Outside off and on a length, Daryl Mitchell punches this one through point for four more.
This one lands fuller and on middle, Daryl Mitchell defends it solidly.
Tossed up delivery, Daryl Mitchell eases it towards the off side for one.
Fuller and on the stumps, this is again defended out solidly.
Full and turning on middle, defended back to the bowler.
Full once again outside off. defended by Daryl Mitchell.
Tossed up on middle and off, Daryl Mitchell defends it towards Jack Leach.
Sliding down leg on a good length, Daryl Mitchell misses his flick.
Flighted on off, worked towards mid-wicket for a single.
Good-length delivery on off. Tom Blundell cuts it towards point.
On off and on a full length, this is blocked out.
This one lands on middle and outside off, Daryl Mitchell eases it towards the mid off fielder.
On off again, this is defended back towards the bowler.
Oh, this was close. Fuller and on leg, Daryl Mitchell flicks it towards the leg side. The fielder at short leg had a difficult chance but couldn't get his hands on it. Single taken.
Close again! On a length and on middle, Tom Blundell looks to defend it but the ball carries towards mid on and just short of the fielder. Tom Blundell gets lucky this time.
This one lands fuller, Tom Blundell defends it back towards the bowler.
Flatter delivery on off. Daryl Mitchell smothers it into the pitch.
Full outside off, Daryl Mitchell gets a stride forward and defends solidly.
Good-length delivery on off stump. Daryl Mitchell stands tall and defends.
Fraction fuller on middle. worked towards short mid on.
On middle of a good length., Daryl Mitchell plays it back down the pitch.
Flighted outside off, Daryl Mitchell comes across the stumps and defends Jack Leach bowls another maiden!
This one lands fuller and on middle, this is defended back towards Joe Root.
On middle again, Tom Blundell eases it towards the mid on fielder.
Tossed up delivery, Tom Blundell defends it solidly.
Joe Root bowls it on off, Tom Blundell blocks it towards the vacant silly point region.
Another fuller and down the middle, Tom Blundell with a solid block.
On middle and leg this time, Blundell flicks that towards mid-wicket for a brace.
Flatter outside off, Daryl Mitchell works it towards cover.
Flights this full on middle. Daryl Mitchell defends it back to the bowler.
Good-length delivery slightly wide, Daryl Mitchell goes on the backfoot and works it to point.
Full once again on leg, Daryl Mitchell firmly plays it back to the bowler.
Faster delivery on a good length outside off. Daryl Mitchell stands tall and punches towards cover.
Flighted full and angling in from off, Daryl Mitchell defends and gets an inside edge towards the leg side.
Broad goes outside off and on a good length, Tom Blundell shoulders arms at it.
Another one outside off, Tom Blundell is happy to let it go.
Oh, that was close! This one lands a bit lower and just outside off, Tom Blundell looks to defend it but misses.

On a length and on off, Tom Blundell blocks it but gets an inside edge and hits his pads. Stuart Broad thinks that it had directly hit his pads and makes a loud appeal but the umpire shows no interest.
Full and outside off, does not get swing this time, Tom Blundell defends solidly.
Fraction back of a length on off, Tom Blundell rises on his toes and plays it back down the pitch. Maiden for Stuart Broad to start of with the new ball!
Matthew Potts starts with a full delivery angling into the pads, Daryl Mitchell flicks this wide of square leg for a single.
Adjusts his length, and pulls it back a bit outside off. Tom Blundell gets his bat down in time as it stays slightly low.
Full once again outside off, Tom Blundell defends it towards cover-point.
FOUR! Tom Blundell makes the most of the loose delivery! Matthew Potts does not nail his yorker, Tom Blundell flicks the full delivery off his pads through mid-wicket for four runs!
Matthew Potts keeps this one outside off and full, Tom Blundell punches it towards cover.
Slightly short and wide from off stump. Tom Blundell strides forward and leaves the ball in style. That will be Lunch on DAY 4!
Full length, outside off. Daryl Mitchell gets behind the line to block it out.
Fraction short, outside off. Daryl Mitchell shoulders his arms at it.
Broad serves it full and outside off. Mitchell shuffles across and blocks it to the off side.
A stifled appeal for lbw but the umpire is unmoved. This one is angled in on off. Daryl Mitchell stays inside the crease. He fends it out to safety awkwardly.
Back of a length, wide outside off. Mitchell leaves it alone.
A maiden for Broad to start the afternoon session. This is on a good length, in the channel. Daryl Mitchell covers his stumps and lets it go through.
Potts goes full and down leg. Blundell tries to flick it away but fails to connect.
Well wide of off stump. Tom Blundell shows no interest.
Three dots on the trot! Length ball, on the pads, this one stays a touch low. Blundell blocks it to the on side.
Touch fuller, on fourth stump. Tom Blundell presses forward and blocks it to point. He denies for a single straightaway.
Fuller length, outside off. Blundell drives it on the up but only manages to find the fielder.
A great start by Potts, just a run of it. It is around the hips. Blundell clips it to deep square leg for a single.

This is close! Broad dishes an inswinger, around off. Blundell tries to drive it down the ground but gets an inside edge. The ball almost goes on to disturb the stumps behind, but Blundell is quick to turn around and keep the ball away.
Fraction short, on off. Blundell stays back and defends it out.
Full length, on fifth stump. Tom Blundell defends it to covers on the front foot and scampers across for a single. He moves to 47.
Much fuller, outside off. Mitchell gets behind the line and smothers it towards mid off.
A length ball, on off. Mitchell tries to defend it out but does more off the inner half.
Full length, on off. Mitchell comes up with a good solid back to the bowler. Just a single off it. It has been a great start by England so far.
Angles it in, full and outside off. Blundell digs it out to point and they cross.
Daryl Mitchell square up a bit and defends this length delivery to point off the outer half.
Short ball, wide outside off. Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone.
Outside off yet again. Daryl Mitchell has no shot to offer.
Potts fires it full and outside off. Mitchell uses his feet and drive it straight to covers.
On a length, on off. Daryl Mitchell defends it back to the bowler with full face of the blade.
Outside off, Blundell shows no interest.
Good length, in the channel. Blundell defends it into the deck with soft hands.
Fraction short, wide outside off. Tom Blundell punches it to cover for a quick single. He moves to 49.
Full length, spraying down leg. Daryl Mitchell flicks it to mid-wicket, unable to get it through the gap.
Broad dishes it full, in the channel. Daryl Mitchell defends it to covers.
BEATEN! This is fuller again, on fifth stump. Daryl Mitchell looks to defend it out but gets beaten on the outside edge. This one also stays a touch low.
Tossed up, on middle and leg. Blundell nudges it to the leg side.
Floated and full, around leg. Blundell gets it to the off side.
Fired down the leg side. Blundell nurdles it to short leg.

GOES PAST SLIPS! This is close. It is tossed up, full and around off. Tom Blundell tries to defend it out on his front foot. He gets a thick outside edge which beates the diving effort of the slip fielder. It races away down to third man for a brace. FIFTY up for Blundell.
On off, defended out.
Sharp turn! Touch short, outside off. Blundell looks to pull it away but decides against it in the end.
FOUR! Off the edge! Full length, in the channel. Daryl Mitchell hangs his blade away from his body and guides it through slip cordon for four. Mitchell gets a bit lucky this time.
On off, blocked out.
Length, around off, defended back to the bowler.
Outside off, left alone by Daryl Mitchell.

FOUR! Deft touch! Daryl Mitchell now gets his fifth Test match half century. It is on a good length, outside off. Daryl Mitchell waits for it and guides it down to third man for a boundary. A fielder gives it a chase but in vain.
Length, on off. Daryl Mitchell gets behind and blocks.
Flatter, on the pads, Tom Blundell goes back and tucks it to square leg.
Fuller and on middle. Blundell defends it into the deck on the front foot.
Short, around off. Blundell goes back and punches it through covers for a single.
On off, defended out.
FOUR! Daryl Mitchell growing with confidence now. It is full and outside off. Daryl Mitchell sweeps it through square leg for a boundary.
Full and on off. Mitchell defends it to covers on the front foot.

NOT OUT! Tom Blundell is saved by the review this time. Full and angling into the pads. Tom Blundell plays all over this one and it thumps against his pads. The umpire raises his finger and Tom Blundell reviews. The Ultra Edge shows no bat is involved. The Ball Tracking shows that the ball is missing the wickets. Yet another decision that favoured England has to be overturned here.
A length delivery on the off, Blundell blocks it on the offside and gets across for a quick single.
A good-length delivery on off, Mitchell blocks it out on the off side.
A bit fuller in length, on middle and leg, Mitchell drives it straight towards the fielder at mid on.

OUT! LBW! This time the review goes in favor of England! Matthew Potts bowls this on a good length outside off, Gets good shape into the batter, as Daryl Mitchell comes across the stumps to work it leg side. Misses the line of the ball and hits him hard on his pads. The umpire says its out once again and Daryl Mitchell reviews this time. There is no edge as confirmed by the UltraEdge and three reds means that the on field decision stays. Daryl Mitchell the man in form trudges back to the pavilion.
Howout: lbw b Matthew Potts

Commentary: A length delivery on off, Bracewell plays a solid front foot defense.
A full delivery on the stumps, Blundell defends it towards short leg.
Another full delivery on the stumps, Blundell blocks it out.

FOUR! Tossed-up delivery on off, Blundell looks to defend it but gets an outside edge as the ball rolls between the keeper and the first slip fielder for a boundary. The fielder at slips tries to make a diving stop but misses.
A length delivery on the off, Blundell goes on the backfoot and pushes it towards covers. He denies for the single.
A bit short, outside off, Blundell cuts it towards deep point for a single.
On a good-length and on the off, Bracewell blocks it out on the off side.
A good-length delivery on the leg stump, Blundell flicks it towards fine leg for a single.
BEATEN! A bit fuller on off, shaping away from the left hander. Bracewell tries to drive at it but misses it completely.
A length delivery on off, Bracewell plays a solid defense.
Another length delivery but this time a bit straight, Bracewell blocks it out to the legside.
Slightly shorter delivery on off, Bracewell defends it off the backfoot.
A full one outside off, shaping away. Bracewell decides to leave it.
A full delivery outside off, Blundell plays a front foot defense.
Full on middle, defended back to the bowler.
On the stumps and much fuller, Blundell takes a stride forward and guides it to the off side.
Tossed-up delivery on middle, Tom Blundell guides it towards the fielder at mid off.
Full and straight down the middle, Blundell blocks it to the leg side.
A maiden from Jack Leach. Slightly short on middle, Blundell goes deep in his crease and defends it away.
Full and angling down leg, Michael Bracewell tries to flick it and it hits his pad, England players appeal but the umpire in unmoved.
A length delivery on the off, Blundell flicks it straight to short mid-wicket.
Good length and on the off, Blundell blocks it straight back to the bowler.
Short this time angling into the batter, Tom Blundell pulls this wide of fine leg for a single.
Good-length on off, Michael Bracewell knocks it to cover.

Good-length delivery outside off, Michael Bracewell punches this through cover-point as the ball runs towards the fence for three runs. The ball seemed to be running away from the fielder but he eventually gets there.
SIX! Tossed up on off, Michael Bracewell gets on his knees and smashes it over long on for a maximum. That was perfectly timed from Michael Bracewell.
Quicker delivery on middle, Bracewell turns it to short leg.

OUT! CAUGHT! Jack Leach strikes and just like in the first innings he picking on the New Zealand tail! This was full and angling into the pads, Michael Bracewell flicks this high towards Zak Crawley at deep square leg who pouches it with ease. Jack Leach raises his arms in celebration as Michael Bracewell was looking to be aggressive!
Howout: c Zak Crawley b Jack Leach

Commentary: Tossed up on middle, Tim Southee guides it towards the slip fielder.
This one lands on middle and fuller, Tim Southee eases it towards mid on fielder.
Tossed up this up outside off, Southee leans forward and drives it aerially at covers. The fielder makes a diving effort but fails to get any hand to it.
On off, defended towards the leg side.
FOUR! Matthew Potts bowls it on a length outside off, Blundell opens his bat face and late cuts it past the slip cordon for a boundary.
On off, defended out.
This one lands on leg, Tom Blundell flicks it towards square leg for a brace.
On a full length and down the middle, Tom Blundell defends it solidly off his front foot.
Oh, that was close! Fuller and outside off, Tom Blundell looks to drive it but misses. The ball just aired past his bat and into the gloves of the keeper.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Tim Southee flicks it towards the leg side and scampers through for a quick single.
Fuller and outside off, Tom Blundell defends it towards the vacant silly point region.
This one lands on middle, Tom Blundell defends it back towards the bowler.
On leg, Tom Blundell sweeps it towards backward square leg. The ball was in the air for some time but falls in no man's land. Single taken.
On off, this is defended towards the short cover fielder.
Dropped! This is outside off, Tim Southee looks to play at but gets an outside edge and carries towards the first slip who drops it. A lucky escape for Tim Southee.
On middle, blocked out.
This is outside off and on a length, Tom Blundell looks to play at it but misses.
On a length and down the middle, this is defended towards the mid on fielder.
This one lands on a length and outside off, Tom Blundell guides it towards backward point for one.
Slightly shorter and on off, Tim Southee looks to defend it but misses. That was close.
Matthew Potts bowls it just outside off, Tim Southee looks to defend it but misses.
On a length with a hint of turn, Tom Blundell looks to defend it but misses.
Fuller and on off, Tom Blundell uses his feet and blocks it away.
FOUR! This one lands outside leg, Tom Blundell sweeps it but gets a bottom edge as the ball races towards the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Outside off this time, Tom Blundell eases it towards the vacant silly point region.
Touch fuller in length and down the middle, Tom Blundell plays it towards the fielder at mid on.
Jack Leach bowls it outside off, Tom Blundell guides it towards the fielder at point.
On a length and outside leg, Tim Southee looks to give it a fine tickle but misses.
On a length and on leg, Tim Southee fumbles a bit but defends it in the end.
Some extra bounce angling into the batter, Tim Southee looks to block it but the ball hits his glove and rolls towards short fine leg. They rotate the strike.
This is on off, Tom Blundell drives it but finds the fielder at short cover.
Slightly shorter and on middle, Tom Blundell dances down the track and looks to pull it but misses. The ball goes past his bat and stumps and into the gloves of the keeper. He gets a lucky escape.
On off, defended out.

OUT! Jack Leach is having a wonderful Test match here! slightly full on middle, turns off the surface, and keeps its line. Tim Southee tries to defend and has a massive gap between bat and pad. The ball goes through that gap and castles him all ends up. Two more wickets left and England will be hoping to end this innings as soon as possible!
Howout: b Jack Leach

Commentary: Outside off this time, Neil Wagner defends it to the short cover fielder.
This one land on off, Neil Wagner defends it solidly.
Jack Leach bowls it just outside off, Neil Wagner looks to drive it but misses. That was close to the stumps.
Fuller and on middle, Neil Wagner eases it back towards the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Not the prettiest of catches but he has managed to hang onto that one! This one is flighted full outside off, Neil Wagner plays at it and gets a thick edge to the keeper. Sam Billings does not get it in his gloves but uses his thighs to clasp the ball. Pulls it out from between his legs like a bunny from the hat and appeals loudly! The umpire wants to check if the catch is caught cleanly and informs that the soft signal is out. The replays go in favour of England and another man departs for New Zealand.
Howout: c Sam Billings b Jack Leach

Commentary: Shorter and on middle, Tom Blundell pulls is towards the fielder at mid-wicket.
On a length and on off, Tom Blundell blocks it away.
Goes fuller and down the leg side, Blundell looks to flick it but the ball hits his pads and rolls toward the vacant short leg region.
This is on off and on a length, Tom Blundell blocks it towards slips.
FOUR! This one lands on middle, Tom Blundell dances down the track and steers it past covers for a boundary.
Shorter one on off, Tom Blundell looks to play at it but misses. Wide called.
FOUR! This one is perfectly timed. Fuller and on off, Tom Blundell uses his feet and drives it past covers for another boundary.
Good-length delivery on off. Worked towards point.
Middle stump line on a good length. Trent Boult plays it back to the bowler.
Full angling into the pads, Trent Boult charges and gets an inside edge towards backward square leg.
Chance for Joe Root at slips! Full and outside off, Trent Boult defends and gets a thick edge towards the diving slip fielder. Does not manage to keep an hold of it.

This one lands outside off, Trent Boult steps out and tries to defend it but gets an inside edge back on his pads. Jack Leach thought it had hit his pads and makes an appeal but the umpire was not interested.
Full on the pads, Defended towards square leg.
Good-length delivery on middle. Tom Blundell gets across the stumps and defends it back to the bowler.
Strays down leg stump this time on a good length. Tom Blundell leaves this one alone.
Full and angling into the pads, Tom Blundell works it to square leg.
FOUR! What wonderful placement from Tom Blundell! Fraction short angling into the batter, Tom Blundell makes room and pierces the two fielders at deep point and fine leg for a boundary.
Back-of-a-length delivery going doing the leg side, Tom Blundell tries to glance this but misses.
FOUR! Tom Blundell with an innovative shot this time! Slightly full outside off, the batter moves way outside off stump and goes low to paddle this over Sam Billings for a boundary!
FOUR! Trent Boult gets this one away! He gives the bowler the charge and catches the ball on the full at his pads. Clobbers this one square of mid-wicket for his first boundary!

OUT! BOWLED! This is on off and fuller with some turn, Trent Boult dances down the track to swing at it but misses. The ball kisses the middle pole and that ends the innings for New Zealand. Jack Leach gets his second 5-wicket haul of the game and the first 10-wicket haul of his Test career! All the English players surround him and rejoice at his achievement. Tom Blundell walks off to a standing ovation for his unbeaten knock and Jack Leach follows him off the ground he loves so much! The players will take Tea on Day 4!
Howout: b Jack Leach

Commentary: Trent Boult starts with a length delivery on the off. Lees defends it straight back to the bowler off the front foot.
On off and on a good length, Alex Lees eases it straight back to the bowler off the back foot.

FOUR! Streaky boundary to get the innings going! Trent Boult goes full outside off and gets Alex Lees to play at it tentatively. Gets a thick outside edge that flies between third slip and gully for a lucky boundary! Alex Lees is off the mark but not in the way he would have hoped for.
Fraction short on off, Alex Lees gets on the backfoot and works it towards point.
Fuller this time outside off. Driven towards cover by Alex Lees.
Full and angling down leg, Alex Lees works this to deep square leg for a single. 5 runs off the first over for England.
FOUR LEG BYES! A loosener from Tim Southee. Bowls it outside leg, Alex Lees looks to flick it but misses. The keeper misses it as well as the ball races behind the fine leg fence off the pads.
Outside off this time, Lees defends it comfortably towards the off side.
Shorter one on off, Alex Lees gets across and blocks it away.
Yorker delivery down the middle, Alex Lees goes on the back foot and blocks it solidly towards the leg side.
On a length angling it into the batter, Alex Lees pushes it straight towards the mid on fielder.
Fuller and on off, Alex Lees leans forward and guides it towards mid on.
Slightly full outside off, angling away from Zak Crawley who is happy to leave it alone.
Gets this one to nip back in. Full and on middle, Zak Crawley plays this towards mid-wicket.
On a good length this time, angling away from off stump. Zak Crawley is watchful as he lets it through to the keeper.
Trent Boult bowls this full on the pads. Zak Crawley punches it towards the mid-on fielder.
Good-length delivery on middle, Zak Crawley shows solid defense as he knocks it towards cover.

FOUR! After playing the over well, Zak Crawley goes for a loose shot! Full and angling away outside off, Zak Crawley swings at the ball but gets the outside edge and the ball flies over the slip towards the third man fence for a boundary.
Fuller delivery on the off, Lees defends it straight back to the bowler.
Full and angling down leg, Alex Lees flicks this towards the diving mid-wicket fielder.
Good-length delivery way outside off, Alex Lees does not play at it.

FOUR! Gets this one away to the boundary though not where he intended it to go! Full and outside off, Alex Lees tries to punch this through covers but does not get this cleanly off his bat. Goes towards backward point for four more runs!
Alex Lees hits the full ball outside off straight towards the cover fielder. Better timing from him this time.
Tim Southee pulls back the length slightly, and bowls it on off, Alex Lees goes back and fends it towards mid on.
Angling into the pads from a good length. Zak Crawley flicks this towards mid-wicket and starts off for a single that is not there. Alex Lees sends him back.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
On a length and just outside off, Zak Crawley gets in two minds but puts a late bat in the end to defend it. The ball bounces through the stumps and towards the keeper.
This one lands on off, Zak Crawley defends it towards the leg side.
On a length and on off, Zak Crawley looks to flick it but misses as the ball hits his pads and rolls towards the vacant silly point region.

RUN OUT! What a disaster for England! Good length delivery on off, Zak Crawley smokes this towards mid off. Both batters ball watching as Kane Williamson makes a brilliant stop and immediately throws it back at the non-strikers end. Alex Lees is left standing in the middle of the pitch as Trent Boult has  the presence of mind to run back to the stumps and collect the throw. What an outstanding overall fielding display from New Zealand and some ordinary running from the English batters!
Howout: run out (Kane Williamson / Trent Boult)

Commentary: This one lands outside off and on a length, Ollie Pope lets it through and towards the keeper.
On a length and on leg, Ollie Pope looks to flick it but the ball hits his pads and rolls towards the leg side. Leg bye taken.
On the pads. On a length and down the leg side, Zak Crawley looks to play at it but misses as the ball hits his pads.
On the pads again. On off and on a length, Zak Crawley looks to block it but misses as the ball hits his pads again.
Lands it outside off this time, Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
Fuller one on off, Zak Crawley drives it but finds the fielder at covers.
On a length and outside off, Ollie Pope lets it alone towards the keeper.
Full and really wide from the stumps. Ollie Pope reaches for it and misses, should be leaving these deliveries alone!
Fraction shorter outside off, Ollie Pope slashes at it and finds the point fielder.
Trent Boult bowls this one full and way outside off stump. Ollie Pope leaves it alone.
Just short of third slip! Trent Boult pitches this full but close to the stumps. Ollie Pope is forced to play at it and gets an edge towards slip.
Full and on middle. Ollie Pope knocks this back down the pitch.
Huge appeal from Tim Southee! Puts this one full outside off, Zak Crawley plays at it and gets a thick inside edge onto his pads.
Solid from Zak Crawley this time. Good-length delivery, angling in from outside off. Defended towards the bowler.
Outside off and fuller in length, Zak Crawley drives it but finds the fielder at short covers.
On a length and outside off, Zak Crawley defends it very late as the ball bounces past the off pole and towards the keeper.

Oh, that was close! On a length and on middle, Zak Crawley looks to swing at it but gets beaten on the inside edge. The ball just goes over the stumps and towards the keeper who just gets his glove on it diving to his left. Leg bye taken.
On off, blocked out.
FOUR! On a length and on leg, Zak Crawley smashes it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Zak Crawley. Fuller and on off this time, Zak Crawley lofts it over covers and towards deep cover for a boundary.
This one lands outside off, Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
FOUR! Sublime! A third boundary in this over. Fuller and on off, Zak Crawley drives it past long off for another boundary.
Outside off this time, left alone by Zak Crawley.
FOUR! 16 off the over and Zak Crawley is on fire! Goes fuller and outside off, Zak Crawley drives it past covers and gets another boundary.
Full and on the leg, Pope knocks it straight to mid on.
Length delivery on the off, Pope drives it but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Good-Length delivery on middle and leg, Pope flicks it towards deep square leg for a double.
Full and on the middle, Pope moves across and defends it down the pitch.
Length delivery outside off, Pope blocks it out.
FOUR! Ollie Pope gets his first boundary! Full delivery on the pads, Ollie Pope gets on his front foot and plays a beautiful on-drive past the fielder for a boundary!
Low full toss on off, Zak Crawley drives it to cover fielder and scampers for a quick single.
On middle this time, Pope guides it towards the leg side for one.
On off with some turn, Zak Crawley dances down the track to play at it but misses.
This one lands fuller and on middle, Zak Crawley defends it towards the leg side.
Fuller and on off with a hint of turn, Zak Crawley looks to sweep it but misses as the ball hits his pads.
FOUR! Gets it right this time. Fuller one on middle, Zak Crawley gets on his knees and slog sweeps it past mid-wicket for a boundary.
Length delivery on the off, Pope drives it straight to mid off.
Good-Length delivery outside off, with a hint of movement, Pope lets it go to the keeper.
Full and on the middle, Pope knocks it towards mid on.
FOUR! Lovely Shot! Full and outside off, Pope leans towards it and just times that through cover and point for a boundary. Ollie Pope is looking much more settled in now.
Good length on middle and leg, Pope tries to flick it but it hits his pads.
Similar to the previous delivery, Length and on the leg, Pope tries to guide it to leg side but it hits his hips.

OUT! CAUGHT! On a length and on off, Zak Crawley looks to drive it but the ball hits the upper part of his bat and carries towards Kane Williamson at mid off who dives and takes it in both hands. Zak Crawley walks away in disappointment. Joe Root is the new batter in.
Howout: c Kane Williamson b Michael Bracewell

Commentary: Joe Root goes for a reverse sweep to start off, Full and outside off., straight to the slip fielder.
Good-length delivery bowled on a middle stump line. Joe Root knocks it back to the bowler.
Shapes up to reverse sweep once again but the ball is not that full and pitching on middle. Nudges it leg side for a single.
FOUR! On off and fuller in length, Ollie Pope drives it past covers for a boundary. This was brilliant and well-timed from Ollie Pope.
This one lands on off, Ollie Pope defends it solidly.
Length delivery on the off, shaping in, Root leaves it alone.
Good length on the off, Root moves across and blocks it towards mid on.
On a length and on off, but this time swinging away from the right hander, Root lets it go through.

England take a really poor review here! Good-length delivery outside off, Joe Root steps outside the line of the stumps and tries to defend it. Misses the in-swinger as it crashes into his pads. New Zealand players erupt and are convinced that this is out. The umpire says the impact is outside off and Kane Williamson reviews this but the umpire has got it bang on! They have lost their review!

Another review lost! This one lands on a length and outside off, Joe Root looks to block it but misses as the ball hits his pads. Loud appeal again but the finger stays down. Kane Williamson has a smile on his face and takes another review. Ball Tracking shows that the impact was outside off in this one as well.
Full delivery on the off, Root moves acroos to the offside and blocks it to short mid-wicket.
Tossed up on middle, this is guided towards mid on for one.
On off this time, Joe Root plays a reverse sweep but finds the fielder at gully.
This one lands on middle, Joe Root flicks it straight towards the fielder at short mid-wicket.
This is full outside off. Joe Root comes across the stumps and clobbers it to deep square leg for a brace.
On middle and fuller, Joe Root sweeps it. The ball hits the pads of the fielder at short leg and rolls back towards the bowler.
Fullish delivery on the stumps, played that towards silly mid-on and towards the fielder.
Length delivery outside off, Pope lets it go through to the keeper.
A bit fuller on the off, Pope blocks it straight down the pitch.
Full and outside off, Pope leans forward and defends it to short covers.
Good-Length delivery on the off, Pope plays a solid defense.
Full and wide outside off, Pope drives it towards point and gets across for a quick single.

Good-length delivery outside off, shaping into Joe Root. Hits his pads again and Tim Southee continues to believe that he has his man! Kane Williamson this time does not bother wasting his final review!
FOUR! Tossed up outside off, Ollie Pope shuffles across and smashes it past point for a boundary.
Outside off again, this is defended off the front foot.
FOUR! Tossed up just outside off with some turn, Ollie Pope waits for the ball and cuts it late. He gets an outside edge as the ball races through and between the keeper and the slips for a boundary.
Turning in on the pads, Pope flicks it to the right of mid-wicket for one.
Tossed up outside off, Root gets down on one knee and sweeps it towards deep square leg for one more.

FOUR! Third boundary of the over! Ollie Pope steps down and catches the ball on the full outside off. He places it past the diving mid off fielder for a lovely boundary. No power here just pure timing! Expensive over as 14 runs were conceded in it.
Full delivery on the off, Root blocks it to short covers.
Full again, wide outside off, Root drives it straight to the cover fielder.
Full delivery outside off, Root puches it but it goes straight to mid off.
Length delivery outside off, Root moves across and defends it well.
Good-Length on the fifth stump, Root lifts his arms and lets it go.
A fraction fuller this time outside off, Root takes a stride forward and square drives it straight to backward point. Oh, its a no ball.
FOUR! Easy pickings for Root. Full and on the leg stump, Root flicks it well on the leg side towards the deep square leg fence for a boundary.
On off, Ollie Pope reverse sweeps it towards the off side for one.
FOUR! On off again, Joe Root connects the reverse sweep this time towards backward point for a boundary.
Lands it on middle, Joe Root defends it towards the short leg fielder.
Flighted delivery outside off, Root looks to reverse sweep it but misses.
This one lands on leg, Joe Root flicks it towards the leg side.
FOUR! Flighted up on off, Joe Root looks to defend it but gets a thick outside edge as it goes through Daryl Mitchell at slips and towards long stop for a boundary.
Full and way wide outside off, Ollie Pope times it well towards cover.
Good-length delivery outside off, angling away. Left alone by Ollie Pope.
Full this time on the pads, worked towards mid-wicket.
Neil Wagner bowls this slower on a good length, on an off stump line. Ollie Pope tries to work this leg side and gets a leading edge uppishly towards mid off.
Outside off once again on a good length. Leaves it for the keeper to gather.
Slightly back of a length on off stump, Joe Root gets on his toes and works it towards backward point.

FOUR! Well watched from Ollie Pope as the ball stays low! Michael Bracewell puts this full on off stump line, Ollie Pope has his eyes on the ball and gets his bat down in time to punch it past the cover fielder for an outstanding boundary!
Tossed up on middle and leg, Ollie Pope flicks it to short fine leg fielder  who makes a diving stop. No runs.
Good-length delivery angling away from off, Ollie Pope gets a good stride forward and defends it towards cover.
Slightly short this time, Pope turns it to short leg.
Flighted up on middle, Pope defends it back towards the bowler.
Tossed up on middle, this is defended towards the mid on fielder.
Full delivery on off, Joe Root defends this solidly.
Fraction fuller and keeps the same line, Joe Root works this towards mid on.
NO BALL! Neil Wagner oversteps and will have to bowl an extra delivery! Full once again outside off, shoots off the surface and Joe Root gloves it towards mid on.
Goes fuller and outside off, Joe Root drives it but finds the fielder at covers.
This one lands on off again, Joe Root drives it towards the mid on fielder this time.
Goes outside off this time, well left by Joe Root.

SIX! What a way to get England to 100. Unbelievable from Root. Outside off and fuller in length, Joe Root plays a reverse scoop over third man for a maximum. Joe Root gives Neil Wagner a friendly smile.
Good-length delivery in line with the stumps, Ollie Pope works it to square leg for a single.
Spinning down leg side away from the batter. Tom Blundell manages to get gloves on it.
Goes short this time and Joe Root goes back on the crease to work it towards square leg for a single.
Tossed up outside off, Ollie Pope defends it solidly.
Goes fuller and outside off, Ollie Pope plays a late cut towards third man for a brace.
Fuller and on middle, this is defended towards the mid on fielder.
Fuller delivery on off, Joe Root fends it back to Neil Wagner.
Full once again at the stumps. Joe Root is strong in defense as he plays it back to the bowler.
Good-length delivery this time on off, Joe Root works this to point,
Goes back to bowling full on the off stump line. Joe Root happy to keep defending.
Full and slightly slow, pitching outside off. Joe Root takes a stride forward and plays it close to his pads.
Neil Wagner is on the floor after his delivery stride. Bowls a full delivery outside off and gets Joe Root to drive. The cover fielder gets to the ball and collects it.
Starts with a length ball on middle, Ollie Pope defends it back towards Trent Boult.
Another length ball around off, this is again defended back towards the bowler.
This one lands outside leg, Ollie Pope looks to flick it but misses as the ball goes towards the keeper.
On a length and outside off, Ollie Pope punches it through covers for a brace.
Shorter one on leg, Ollie Pope pulls it towards fine leg. The ball fell just short of the fielder who makes a diving stop on the boundary line. They rotate the strike.
This is on middle, Joe Root blocks it solidly.
FOUR! Gets this one just past the backward point fielder! Neil Wagner goes full outside off, Ollie Pope swings at it hard and gets a thick edge that flies to the deep backward square boundary!
Full once again outside off. Knocks it towards short cover.
Neil Wagner sticking to the outside off line and Ollie Pope continues to play at it. Works this towards covers.
Ollie Pope opens the face of the bat and works this full delivery towards backward point.
Full once again outside off. Ollie Pope is unable to find the gap through covers.
Closer to the stumps this time but still full. Mistimes his shot towards mid on.
On a length and down the middle, Joe Root defends it away.
Good-length delivery around off, Joe Root eases it towards the off side.
This one lands a bit lower and outside off, Joe Root looks to play at it but gets beaten off the bottom edge.
Oh, that was close again. Outside off again, Joe Root looks to drive it but gets a thick bottom edge as the ball rolls towards the leg side. They rotate the strike.
Trent Boult serves it on off, this is defended out solidly.
Touch fuller and on middle, Ollie Pope flicks it towards the leg side and straight towards the fielder.
Tim Southee begins with a full delivery on middle, Joe Root works this wide off mid on for a single.
Full angling into the pads. Ollie Pope flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good-length delivery on off. Ollie Pope comes down the wicket and knocks it back to the bowler.

FOUR! That is Fifty for Ollie Pope! He has played some tremendous shots this innings but gets to his half century with a lucky inside edge towards the boundary! Tim Southee bowls this on a good length and outside off, Ollie Pope plays at it and gets a thick inside edge past Tom Blundell to reach the fine leg boundary and get to his 7th Test half century!
Full and outside off, drives once again towards cover and a misfield allows a single.
Fraction back of a length outside off, Joe Root leaves this alone.
Slightly shorter and on off, Ollie Pope pulls it towards the fielder at short mid-wicket.
This is much fuller and on leg, Ollie Pope flicks it towards square leg for one.
Shorter and on middle, Joe Root pulls it towards backward square leg. The fielder reacts it late but does well to stop it in the end. A couple of runs taken.
This is on a length and down the middle, Joe Root blocks it out solidly.
Slightly shorter in length, Joe Root flicks it towards the fielder at fine leg. They rotate the strike.
This one lands outside off, Ollie Pope is happy to let it go.
Slightly full on middle and off. Joe Root is solid in defense.
FOUR! Joe Root is seeing the ball really well! Tim Southee bangs this short to try a bounce out Joe Root! He rolls his wrist and dispatches it to the backward square leg boundary for for more runs!
Full and angling into the pads, Joe Root works this to square leg for a single.
Lovely placement from Ollie Pope, as he works the full delivery outside off, towards the fine leg boundary! A half stop in the circle saves one as they run three.
Shaping in from outside off and bowled on a good length. Ollie Pope is happy to let this one through.

A shade fuller angling towards the leg stump, Ollie Pope tries to work this leg side and misses the ball. Hits the pads and Tim Southee just wants something to go his way. Umpire reckons its missing and Kane Williamson does not review. Replays show the ball is going over the stumps.
On a length and on middle, Ollie Pope pulls it towards the fielder at fine leg who makes a diving stop on the boundary line. A couple of runs taken.
This is fuller and outside off, Ollie Pope defends it towards the off side.
Wayward bouncer this time, Ollie Pope ducks underneath it.
On a length and on off, Ollie Pope punches it towards the fielder at point.
Touch fuller delivery on off, Ollie Pope drives towards the cover fielder and take one.
Good-length delivery on leg, Joe Root pulls it towards square leg for one.
Good-length delivery outside off, Joe Root goes across the stumps and works it fine leg for a single.
On a good length once again wide from the stumps. Ollie Pope defends this easily.
Slightly full and angled into the pads. Ollie Pope tucks this to square leg.
Ollie Pope gets beaten this time. Full and outside off, gets movement this time and beats the bat of Ollie Pope
Slightly back of a length on middle. Ollie Pope works this towards mid-wicket.
Really wide from the stumps on a good length. Ollie Pope watches it go through and shows his back to the bowler.
Fuller one on middle and leg, Joe Root flicks it towards backward square leg for one.
Tosses it up on middle, Ollie Pope flicks it towards the fielder at leg gully.
On off this time, Ollie Pope defends it towards the mid on fielder.
This one lands on off again, Ollie Pope guides it to mid on for one.
Michael Bracewell bowls it on off again, Joe Root plays a reverse sweep towards backward point for a brace.
Tossed up delivery, Joe Root defends it solidly off his front foot.
Tim Southee goes full outside off. Ollie Pope taps it towards short cover.
Good-length delivery outside off stump. Ollie Pope comes towards the off side and fends it towards gully.
Good-length delivery going down leg, Ollie Pope misses the line of the ball and raps him on his pads.

Sublime timing from Ollie Pope! Sees the ball full and wide outside off, opens the face of his bat, and places it through cover-point for three runs. Outstanding fielding from Devon Conway saves a run!
Pitched full on off, Joe Root dabs it back to the bowler.
Close to off stump on a good length, Joe Root has complete control of his defense.
This one lands fuller and outside off, Ollie Pope guides it to point for one.

FOUR! On off again, Joe Root plays a reverse sweep but gets a top edge and the ball carries towards slips. A difficult catch for Daryl Mitchell to his left who just gets his hands at it as the ball races the third man fence.
Outside off, blocked out.
This one lands on off, Joe Root punches it to covers for one.
This one is a bit lower with some turn, Ollie Pope looks to block it but the ball hits his pads.
Flighted up on off again, Ollie Pope plays a reverse sweep towards backward point for one.
Wagner begins with a wide delivery outside off on a good length. Ollie Pope leaves it alone.
A touch fuller but still wide. Ollie Pope slashes at it and finds the backward point fielder.

FOUR! 100 partnership between Ollie Pope and Joe Root! Neil Wagner goes shot angling into the batter, Ollie Pope gets on top of this and pulls it between the fine leg and square leg fielder. These two are taking England home and are looking really good out there!
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries! Neil Wagner is all over the place, bowls this one wide outside off. Ollie Pope slashes at it and gets a thick edge towards the third man boundary to get four more runs!
FOUR! Make that three! In complete control of this one is Ollie Pope as he comes forward and punches a full delivery past the mid off fielder to get his third consecutive boundary!
Gets this on a good length angling into the pads, Ollie Pope works this through mid-wicket for a brace.
Goes 'round the wicket and bowls it on off, Joe Root plays a reverse sweep towards backward point for one.
On middle this time, Ollie Pope flicks it on the leg side for one.
FOUR LEG BYES! On leg and much fuller, Joe Root looks to play a reverse sweep but misses. The keeper misses it as well as the ball races the long stop fence.
Goes on middle with some turn, Joe Root again looks to play a reverse sweep but the ball hits his glove and rolls towards short leg.
On off this time, Root plays a reverse sweep again towards backward point for one.
Fuller one on middle, Ollie Pope flicks it towards square leg for a single.
Neil Wagner goes around the wicket and bowls it full on off, Ollie Pope plays it towards mid off.
Goes full angling down leg stump. Ollie Pope flicks this one to fine leg for a single.
Good-length delivery outside off stump, Joe Root shoulders his arms to this one.
Beaten this time! Joe Root goes searching for a full delivery outside off, the ball shapes away and beats his outside edge.
Full delivery aimed for the stumps, Joe Root gets forward and works it to square leg for a single.
Good-length delivery on middle. Ollie Pope punches this towards mid on.
Tossed up on middle, this is defended back towards the bowler.
On leg this time, Joe Root looks to sweep it but fails to connect well.
FOUR! This brings 50 up for Joe Root and he gets a standing ovation. On a length and on leg, Joe Root just gives it a fine tickle as it goes towards the fine leg for a boundary.
FOUR! A poor delivery from Michael Bracewell. On a length and on leg, slower too, Joe Root pulls it hard towards backward square leg for a boundary.
On middle again, Joe Root sweeps it towards leg side for one.
Fuller one on leg, Ollie Pope flicks it towards backward square leg for one. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 4.
Starts with a length delivery, Ollie Pope works it towards leg side for one.
This is a fuller delivery, drifting on the legs tump, Joe Root flicks it away straight to the short mid wicket fielder.
On a full length again, Joe Root nudges it towards the leg side for one.
On a good length delivery, angling back in, Pope covers the line and defends it.

OUT! BOWLED! What a magnificent ball. This one lands outside off and nips back in a long way and knocks over the off pole! Ollie Pope misses it with the intention to block it and New Zealand have an early and much needed breakthrough.
Howout: b Tim Southee

Commentary: Fraction full on off stump, Jonny Bairstow defends it towards cover.
Around the wicket on a good length and wide from off stump. Joe Root leaves this one alone.
FOUR! First boundary of the day! Slightly back of a length outside off, Joe Root is not going to miss out on this as he slashes it hard towards the deep point fence for a boundary!

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Joe Root! This one is placed elagantly through cover-point to get England moving on Day 5. Trent Boult bowls this on a good length outside off and gets the treatment.
Straying down leg side on a good length, Joe Root works this to fine leg for a single.

FOUR! Jonny Bairstow is off the mark with a boundary! This is full and angling into the pads, Jonny Bairstow is a man in form as he times it to perfection through square leg for a boundary! Jonny Bairstow is up and going so fasten your seat belts!

FOUR! Make that four boundaries in an over! Trent Boult has conceded 17 runs in his first over of Day 5 and not hit his stride! This one is short and wide outside off, Jonny Bairstow guides this past the infield to deep backward point and collects four more runs! England now need only 94 runs!
On a length shaping it away from the batter, Joe Root looks to block it but misses.
Goes much fuller this time and on off, Joe Root flicks it but finds the fielder at mid on.
On a length angling it away, Joe Root looks to block this one as well but misses.
On off and on a length, Joe Root guides it towards the gully fielder.
On a length and on off, Joe Root defends it towards the off side.
Outside off this time, Joe Root defends it with soft hands.
Trent Boult has been poor today! This one is also straying down leg and full, Jonny Bairstow flicks this through square leg for a brace.

FOUR! Jonny Bairstow already has three boundaries to his name! This one is full as well outside off. Jonny Bairstow puts a stride forward and clobbers it through the gap in covers for a boundary! This is getting easy for England now!
Trent Boult changes the angle and goes 'round the wicket, bowls it on a good length angling into off. Jonny Bairstow works this towards mid-wicket.
Fraction short and outside off, Jonny Bairstow knocks this towards point.

The best delivery Trent Boult has bowled so far on Day 5! Goes wide of the crease and angles the ball into the batter from a good length. The ball keeps its line and beats Jonny Bairstow on its way to the keeper.
Good-length delivery angling into middle, Jonny Bairstow works this past square leg for single.
Good-Length on middle stump, Bairstow looks to pull it but misses and it hits his body.
A bit fuller on the off, Bairstow drives it straight to covers.
SIX! Jonny Bairstow looks in a hurry. Southee goes full on the off, Bairstow just lofts it over the long off fence for a maximum.
LEG BYE! On a length and on middle and leg, Bairtstow tries to flick it but misses. Huge appeal from the fielders but the umpire is not interested.
On a length and on leg, Root flicks it towards deep square leg for a single.
Length delivery outside off, Bairstow blocks it off to point.
Fuller on the leg stump, Root, pushes it to the leg side for a single.
A bit short on the middle, Bairstow pulls it towards fine leg for a run.
Full delivery on the off, Root moves across and knocks it towards mid on for a single.

FOUR LEG BYES! Trent Boult is not looking in any rhythm here! The ball is short but does not rise much, as Jonny Bairstow tries to pull this fine down the leg side. Misses but gets enough thigh pad on it for it to run towards the fine leg boundary!
On a length and on middle, Bairstow pushes it on the leg side for a single.
Good - Length on the off, Root blocks it to the offside.
Length delivery on the off, Bairstow tries to flick it but gets an inside edge and it goes to fine leg. They get a single.
On a length and on off, Root plays it on the leg side and gets across for a quick single.
Another length delivery on off, Bairstow pushes it towards mid on for a run.
Full delivery on the leg, Root flicks it from his pads towards deep square leg fence for a brace.
Good-Length delivery on off, angling away, Root decides to leave it.
Full delivery on off, Root goes unorthodox and plays a reverse scoop, but finds the fielder.
FOUR! Jonny Bairstow is going after the spinner here! Full and outside off, the batter gets down on his knees and sweeps it over square leg for another boundary! England needs 62 more runs to win!
Fuller delivery outside off, Bairstow tries to play the same shot but this time gets an top edge and it goes towards fine leg. They get three runs for that.
Quicker delivery outside off, Root looks to sweep it but misses and wears it on the front pad. A half-hearted appeal from Michael Bracewell but the finger stays down.
Length and on off, Root blocks it on the offside.
Good length and on the off stump, Root scoops it to fine leg for a single.
On a length outside off which turns in sharply, Jonny Bairstow looks to play at it but the ball hits his glove and rolls towards the leg side. A quick single taken.
This one was close! Good length delivery on the off, Bairstow tries to block, but the ball nips in and there is some extra bounce. Gets an inside edge that misses the off stump but only just!
Fuller and on off, Jonny Bairstow has hardly played a defensive shot this game! He lofts this one over mid on and gets three runs as the fielder runs towards the boundary and stops it.

FOUR! Joe Root does not want to miss this party! Full delivery on the off, Root strides across to the off side and flicks to the square leg fence for a boundary. Root has looked at ease in this entire innings!
Length and on the off, Root plays a front foot defense on the off side.
Full and on the leg stump, Root moves across and plays it to fine leg for a single.

FOUR! Another boundary for Bairstow. Southee goes short and wide on the off, Bairstow waits for the ball and plays a late cut past slip cordon and toward the third man fence for boundary. England are now achieving this target at a canter!
Full and outside off, Root sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
LEG BYE! Full once again on off, Bairstow tries to reverse sweep but misses and it hits him on the leg. They get across for a single.
Tossed-up delivery, Joe Root gets on his knees and sweeps it towards square leg for one.
SIX! Massive hit. Tossed up outside off, Bairstow charges down the pitch and lofts it above the bowler over the long on fence for a maximium. Just 36 more runs to complete the whitewash!
Length and on off, Bairstow tries to heave it over mid-wicket but misses it completely.
Full and on the off, Bairstow plays a one handed sweep towards deep mid-wicket for a single.

FOUR! That is the second-fastest half-century by an England batter in Test cricket! What a game Jonny Bairstow has had as he follows up his first innings master class with a quick-fire innings to seal England's run chase! Tim Southee bowls this fraction full in line with the stumps and it has been dispatched straight over the non striker to the long on fence! Jonny Bairstow gets his 23rd Test fifty and he is at complete ease!
Good length on the middle, a bit slower, Bairstow pushes it to the leg side and gets two runs. Good running between the wickets.
Good-Length delivery outside off, Bairstow tries to play at it but misses it.
Length and on the off, Bairstow knocks it straight to point.
Full and on the leg, Bairstow flicks it towards deep square leg for a brace.
A bit fuller on off, Bairstow tries to drive it but misses it.
Full and on the leg, Root pushes it to the leg side for a single.

New Zealand lose their final review! This one is full and bowled on a middle stump line. Jonny Bairstow tries to reverse sweep this but the ball balloons off his arm straight towards slip. New Zealand players celebrate but there is complete confusion as the umpire remains unmoved! Kane Williamson takes the review and replays show that the ball has hit just below the elbow! The on-field decision remains and the umpire tells New Zealand they have lost their review with a smile on his face!
FOUR! Short and outside off, Bairstow gave himself some room by going to the leg side. He smashes it past the point fielder for another boundary. Just 22 runs more needed!
Slower through the air, just outside the off stump, Bairstow looks to play at it but misses.
Flighted up on middle, this is worked towards mid-wicket for one.
Tossed up on middle, Joe Root defends it with soft hands.
Full and on the off, Bairstow leans forward and blocks it to point.
Good length delivery on the off, Bairstow cuts it but could find the gap.
A bit fuller on the leg stump, Baitstow flicks it towards deep square leg for a single.

There is some pre-meditation from both batter and bowler! Joe Root shapes up to go behind the keeper and Tim Southee sees this and bowls a low full toss going down leg side. Joe Root misses and so does the keeper and England get four extra runs through byes!
Length delivery outside off, Root comes across but does not play a shot at it.
Southee tries to bowl a yorker, but it ends being a low full toss on the middle stump, Root easily flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Quicker through the air, on the leg stump, Root flicks it away, straight to the mid wicket fielder.
On off stump, Root misses the shot and gets trapped in front. A slight appeal but the finger stays down.
Tossed up delivery, outside off stump, Root pads it away and defends it.
Tossed up, on the stumps, Root blocks it with soft hands.
FOUR! Tossed up, on the leg stumps, Root sweeps this brilliantly past the deep square leg for a boundary
Quicker and on the stumps, Root works it towards the leg side for a single
On a length and on leg, Root tries to play at it but could not connect.
Full and on the middle, Root blocks it straight back to the bowler.
Good-length delivery on outside off, Worked towards the point fielder.
Full and angling into the pads, Joe Root flicks this towards mid-wicket.
Wide outside off on a good length. Joe Root is happy to see this one go through to the keeper.
Neil Wagner angles this one in from off on a good length, Joe Root plays this confidently towards cover.

FOUR! Short and wide and asking to be hit! Michael Bracewell seems like he wants to help England get home quickly. Bowls a half-tracker that is punched through covers for a boundary! England is just one hit away!

SIX! And that is it! Jonny Bairstow gets England home in style! Michael Bracewell goes full this time angling in from middle, Jonny Bairstow says thank you and pounds this over long on for a biggie! Raises his arm in celebration and the English dressing room is on their feet applauding their players! This has been way too easy today and Jonny Bairstow seems like he can do nothing wrong!
